86 /**
87  * Wrap a given time stamp, if there is an indication for an overflow
88  *
89  * @param st stream
90  * @param timestamp the time stamp to wrap
91  * @return resulting time stamp
92  */
93 static int64_t wrap_timestamp(const AVStream *st, int64_t timestamp)
94 {
95  if (st->pts_wrap_behavior != AV_PTS_WRAP_IGNORE &&
96  st->pts_wrap_reference != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && timestamp != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
97  if (st->pts_wrap_behavior == AV_PTS_WRAP_ADD_OFFSET &&
98  timestamp < st->pts_wrap_reference)
99  return timestamp + (1ULL << st->pts_wrap_bits);
100  else if (st->pts_wrap_behavior == AV_PTS_WRAP_SUB_OFFSET &&
101  timestamp >= st->pts_wrap_reference)
102  return timestamp - (1ULL << st->pts_wrap_bits);
103  }
104  return timestamp;
105 }

145 int ff_copy_whiteblacklists(AVFormatContext *dst, const AVFormatContext *src)
146 {
147  av_assert0(!dst->codec_whitelist &&
148  !dst->format_whitelist &&
149  !dst->protocol_whitelist &&
150  !dst->protocol_blacklist);
151  dst-> codec_whitelist = av_strdup(src->codec_whitelist);
152  dst->format_whitelist = av_strdup(src->format_whitelist);
153  dst->protocol_whitelist = av_strdup(src->protocol_whitelist);
154  dst->protocol_blacklist = av_strdup(src->protocol_blacklist);
155  if ( (src-> codec_whitelist && !dst-> codec_whitelist)
156  || (src-> format_whitelist && !dst-> format_whitelist)
157  || (src->protocol_whitelist && !dst->protocol_whitelist)
158  || (src->protocol_blacklist && !dst->protocol_blacklist)) {
159  av_log(dst, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Failed to duplicate black/whitelist\n");
160  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
161  }
162  return 0;
163 }

165 static const AVCodec *find_decoder(AVFormatContext *s, const AVStream *st, enum AVCodecID codec_id)
166 {
167 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
168 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
169  if (st->codec->codec)
170  return st->codec->codec;
171 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
172 #endif
173 
174  switch (st->codecpar->codec_type) {
175  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
176  if (s->video_codec) return s->video_codec;
177  break;
178  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
179  if (s->audio_codec) return s->audio_codec;
180  break;
181  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE:
182  if (s->subtitle_codec) return s->subtitle_codec;
183  break;
184  }
185 
186  return avcodec_find_decoder(codec_id);
187 }
188 
189 static const AVCodec *find_probe_decoder(AVFormatContext *s, const AVStream *st, enum AVCodecID codec_id)
190 {
191  const AVCodec *codec;
192 
193 #if CONFIG_H264_DECODER
194  /* Other parts of the code assume this decoder to be used for h264,
195  * so force it if possible. */
196  if (codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264)
197  return avcodec_find_decoder_by_name("h264");
198 #endif
199 
200  codec = find_decoder(s, st, codec_id);
201  if (!codec)
202  return NULL;
203 
204  if (codec->capabilities & AV_CODEC_CAP_AVOID_PROBING) {
205  const AVCodec *probe_codec = NULL;
206  while (probe_codec = av_codec_next(probe_codec)) {
207  if (probe_codec->id == codec_id &&
208  av_codec_is_decoder(probe_codec) &&
209  !(probe_codec->capabilities & (AV_CODEC_CAP_AVOID_PROBING | AV_CODEC_CAP_EXPERIMENTAL))) {
210  return probe_codec;
211  }
212  }
213  }
214 
215  return codec;
216 }

223 /* an arbitrarily chosen "sane" max packet size -- 50M */
224 #define SANE_CHUNK_SIZE (50000000)
225 
226 int ffio_limit(AVIOContext *s, int size)
227 {
228  if (s->maxsize>= 0) {
229  int64_t remaining= s->maxsize - avio_tell(s);
230  if (remaining < size) {
231  int64_t newsize = avio_size(s);
232  if (!s->maxsize || s->maxsize<newsize)
233  s->maxsize = newsize - !newsize;
234  remaining= s->maxsize - avio_tell(s);
235  remaining= FFMAX(remaining, 0);
236  }
237 
238  if (s->maxsize>= 0 && remaining+1 < size) {
239  av_log(NULL, remaining ? AV_LOG_ERROR : AV_LOG_DEBUG, "Truncating packet of size %d to %"PRId64"\n", size, remaining+1);
240  size = remaining+1;
241  }
242  }
243  return size;
244 }
245 
246 /* Read the data in sane-sized chunks and append to pkt.
247  * Return the number of bytes read or an error. */
248 static int append_packet_chunked(AVIOContext *s, AVPacket *pkt, int size)
249 {
250  int64_t orig_pos = pkt->pos; // av_grow_packet might reset pos
251  int orig_size = pkt->size;
252  int ret;
253 
254  do {
255  int prev_size = pkt->size;
256  int read_size;
257 
258  /* When the caller requests a lot of data, limit it to the amount
259  * left in file or SANE_CHUNK_SIZE when it is not known. */
260  read_size = size;
261  if (read_size > SANE_CHUNK_SIZE/10) {
262  read_size = ffio_limit(s, read_size);
263  // If filesize/maxsize is unknown, limit to SANE_CHUNK_SIZE
264  if (s->maxsize < 0)
265  read_size = FFMIN(read_size, SANE_CHUNK_SIZE);
266  }
267 
268  ret = av_grow_packet(pkt, read_size);
269  if (ret < 0)
270  break;
271 
272  ret = avio_read(s, pkt->data + prev_size, read_size);
273  if (ret != read_size) {
274  av_shrink_packet(pkt, prev_size + FFMAX(ret, 0));
275  break;
276  }
277 
278  size -= read_size;
279  } while (size > 0);
280  if (size > 0)
281  pkt->flags |= AV_PKT_FLAG_CORRUPT;
282 
283  pkt->pos = orig_pos;
284  if (!pkt->size)
285  av_packet_unref(pkt);
286  return pkt->size > orig_size ? pkt->size - orig_size : ret;
287 }
288 
289 int av_get_packet(AVIOContext *s, AVPacket *pkt, int size)
290 {
291  av_init_packet(pkt);
292  pkt->data = NULL;
293  pkt->size = 0;
294  pkt->pos = avio_tell(s);
295 
296  return append_packet_chunked(s, pkt, size);
297 }
298 
299 int av_append_packet(AVIOContext *s, AVPacket *pkt, int size)
300 {
301  if (!pkt->size)
302  return av_get_packet(s, pkt, size);
303  return append_packet_chunked(s, pkt, size);
304 }

313 static int set_codec_from_probe_data(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
314  AVProbeData *pd)
315 {
316  static const struct {
317  const char *name;
318  enum AVCodecID id;
319  enum AVMediaType type;
320  } fmt_id_type[] = {
321  { "aac", AV_CODEC_ID_AAC, AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO },
322  { "ac3", AV_CODEC_ID_AC3, AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO },
323  { "dts", AV_CODEC_ID_DTS, AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO },
324  { "dvbsub", AV_CODEC_ID_DVB_SUBTITLE,AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE },
325  { "dvbtxt", AV_CODEC_ID_DVB_TELETEXT,AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE },
326  { "eac3", AV_CODEC_ID_EAC3, AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO },
327  { "h264", AV_CODEC_ID_H264, AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO },
328  { "hevc", AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC, AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO },
329  { "loas", AV_CODEC_ID_AAC_LATM, AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO },
330  { "m4v", AV_CODEC_ID_MPEG4, AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO },
331  { "mjpeg_2000",AV_CODEC_ID_JPEG2000, AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO },
332  { "mp3", AV_CODEC_ID_MP3, AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO },
333  { "mpegvideo", AV_CODEC_ID_MPEG2VIDEO, AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO },
334  { "truehd", AV_CODEC_ID_TRUEHD, AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO },
335  { 0 }
336  };
337  int score;
338  AVInputFormat *fmt = av_probe_input_format3(pd, 1, &score);
339 
340  if (fmt) {
341  int i;
342  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
343  "Probe with size=%d, packets=%d detected %s with score=%d\n",
344  pd->buf_size, MAX_PROBE_PACKETS - st->probe_packets,
345  fmt->name, score);
346  for (i = 0; fmt_id_type[i].name; i++) {
347  if (!strcmp(fmt->name, fmt_id_type[i].name)) {
348  if (fmt_id_type[i].type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO &&
349  st->codecpar->sample_rate)
350  continue;
351  if (st->request_probe > score &&
352  st->codecpar->codec_id != fmt_id_type[i].id)
353  continue;
354  st->codecpar->codec_id = fmt_id_type[i].id;
355  st->codecpar->codec_type = fmt_id_type[i].type;
356  st->internal->need_context_update = 1;
357 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
358 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
359  st->codec->codec_type = st->codecpar->codec_type;
360  st->codec->codec_id = st->codecpar->codec_id;
361 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
362 #endif
363  return score;
364  }
365  }
366  }
367  return 0;
368 }

373 int av_demuxer_open(AVFormatContext *ic) {
374  int err;
375 
376  if (ic->format_whitelist && av_match_list(ic->iformat->name, ic->format_whitelist, ',') <= 0) {
377  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Format not on whitelist \'%s\'\n", ic->format_whitelist);
378  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
379  }
380 
381  if (ic->iformat->read_header) {
382  err = ic->iformat->read_header(ic);
383  if (err < 0)
384  return err;
385  }
386 
387  if (ic->pb && !ic->internal->data_offset)
388  ic->internal->data_offset = avio_tell(ic->pb);
389 
390  return 0;
391 }
392 
393 /* Open input file and probe the format if necessary. */
394 static int init_input(AVFormatContext *s, const char *filename,
395  AVDictionary **options)
396 {
397  int ret;
398  AVProbeData pd = { filename, NULL, 0 };
399  int score = AVPROBE_SCORE_RETRY;
400 
401  if (s->pb) {
402  s->flags |= AVFMT_FLAG_CUSTOM_IO;
403  if (!s->iformat)
404  return av_probe_input_buffer2(s->pb, &s->iformat, filename,
405  s, 0, s->format_probesize);
406  else if (s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOFILE)
407  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "Custom AVIOContext makes no sense and "
408  "will be ignored with AVFMT_NOFILE format.\n");
409  return 0;
410  }
411 
412  if ((s->iformat && s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOFILE) ||
413  (!s->iformat && (s->iformat = av_probe_input_format2(&pd, 0, &score))))
414  return score;
415 
416  if ((ret = s->io_open(s, &s->pb, filename, AVIO_FLAG_READ | s->avio_flags, options)) < 0)
417  return ret;
418 
419  if (s->iformat)
420  return 0;
421  return av_probe_input_buffer2(s->pb, &s->iformat, filename,
422  s, 0, s->format_probesize);
423 }
424 
425 static int add_to_pktbuf(AVPacketList **packet_buffer, AVPacket *pkt,
426  AVPacketList **plast_pktl, int ref)
427 {
428  AVPacketList *pktl = av_mallocz(sizeof(AVPacketList));
429  int ret;
430 
431  if (!pktl)
432  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
433 
434  if (ref) {
435  if ((ret = av_packet_ref(&pktl->pkt, pkt)) < 0) {
436  av_free(pktl);
437  return ret;
438  }
439  } else {
440  pktl->pkt = *pkt;
441  }
442 
443  if (*packet_buffer)
444  (*plast_pktl)->next = pktl;
445  else
446  *packet_buffer = pktl;
447 
448  /* Add the packet in the buffered packet list. */
449  *plast_pktl = pktl;
450  return 0;
451 }

453 int avformat_queue_attached_pictures(AVFormatContext *s)
454 {
455  int i, ret;
456  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++)
457  if (s->streams[i]->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC &&
458  s->streams[i]->discard < AVDISCARD_ALL) {
459  if (s->streams[i]->attached_pic.size <= 0) {
460  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
461  "Attached picture on stream %d has invalid size, "
462  "ignoring\n", i);
463  continue;
464  }
465 
466  ret = add_to_pktbuf(&s->internal->raw_packet_buffer,
467  &s->streams[i]->attached_pic,
468  &s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_end, 1);
469  if (ret < 0)
470  return ret;
471  }
472  return 0;
473 }
474 
475 static int update_stream_avctx(AVFormatContext *s)
476 {
477  int i, ret;
478  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
479  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
480 
481  if (!st->internal->need_context_update)
482  continue;
483 
484  /* close parser, because it depends on the codec */
485  if (st->parser && st->internal->avctx->codec_id != st->codecpar->codec_id) {
486  av_parser_close(st->parser);
487  st->parser = NULL;
488  }
489 
490  /* update internal codec context, for the parser */
491  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->internal->avctx, st->codecpar);
492  if (ret < 0)
493  return ret;
494 
495 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
496 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
497  /* update deprecated public codec context */
498  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->codec, st->codecpar);
499  if (ret < 0)
500  return ret;
501 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
502 #endif
503 
504  st->internal->need_context_update = 0;
505  }
506  return 0;
507 }

509 //+: Open an input stream and read the header. The codecs are not opened.
510 //+: The stream must be closed with avformat_close_input().
511 int avformat_open_input(AVFormatContext **ps, const char *filename,
512  AVInputFormat *fmt, AVDictionary **options)
513 {
514  AVFormatContext *s = *ps;
515  int i, ret = 0;
516  AVDictionary *tmp = NULL;
517  ID3v2ExtraMeta *id3v2_extra_meta = NULL;
518 
519  if (!s && !(s = avformat_alloc_context()))
520  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
521  if (!s->av_class) {
522  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Input context has not been properly allocated by avformat_alloc_context() and is not NULL either\n");
523  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
524  }
525  if (fmt)
526  s->iformat = fmt;
527 
528  if (options)
529  av_dict_copy(&tmp, *options, 0);
530 
531  if (s->pb) // must be before any goto fail
532  s->flags |= AVFMT_FLAG_CUSTOM_IO;
533 
534  if ((ret = av_opt_set_dict(s, &tmp)) < 0)
535  goto fail;
536 
537  //+: probe format
538  if ((ret = init_input(s, filename, &tmp)) < 0)
539  goto fail;
540  s->probe_score = ret;
541 
542  if (!s->protocol_whitelist && s->pb && s->pb->protocol_whitelist) {
543  s->protocol_whitelist = av_strdup(s->pb->protocol_whitelist);
544  if (!s->protocol_whitelist) {
545  ret = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
546  goto fail;
547  }
548  }
549 
550  if (!s->protocol_blacklist && s->pb && s->pb->protocol_blacklist) {
551  s->protocol_blacklist = av_strdup(s->pb->protocol_blacklist);
552  if (!s->protocol_blacklist) {
553  ret = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
554  goto fail;
555  }
556  }
557 
558  if (s->format_whitelist && av_match_list(s->iformat->name, s->format_whitelist, ',') <= 0) {
559  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Format not on whitelist \'%s\'\n", s->format_whitelist);
560  ret = AVERROR(EINVAL);
561  goto fail;
562  }
563 
564  avio_skip(s->pb, s->skip_initial_bytes);
565 
566  /* Check filename in case an image number is expected. */
567  if (s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NEEDNUMBER) {
568  if (!av_filename_number_test(filename)) {
569  ret = AVERROR(EINVAL);
570  goto fail;
571  }
572  }
573 
574  s->duration = s->start_time = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
575  av_strlcpy(s->filename, filename ? filename : "", sizeof(s->filename));
576 
577  /* Allocate private data. */
578  if (s->iformat->priv_data_size > 0) {
579  if (!(s->priv_data = av_mallocz(s->iformat->priv_data_size))) {
580  ret = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
581  goto fail;
582  }
583  if (s->iformat->priv_class) {
584  *(const AVClass **) s->priv_data = s->iformat->priv_class;
585  av_opt_set_defaults(s->priv_data);
586  if ((ret = av_opt_set_dict(s->priv_data, &tmp)) < 0)
587  goto fail;
588  }
589  }
590 
591  /* e.g. AVFMT_NOFILE formats will not have a AVIOContext */
592  if (s->pb)
593  ff_id3v2_read(s, ID3v2_DEFAULT_MAGIC, &id3v2_extra_meta, 0);
594 
595  if (!(s->flags&AVFMT_FLAG_PRIV_OPT) && s->iformat->read_header)
596  if ((ret = s->iformat->read_header(s)) < 0)
597  goto fail;
598 
599  if (id3v2_extra_meta) {
600  if (!strcmp(s->iformat->name, "mp3") || !strcmp(s->iformat->name, "aac") ||
601  !strcmp(s->iformat->name, "tta")) {
602  if ((ret = ff_id3v2_parse_apic(s, &id3v2_extra_meta)) < 0)
603  goto fail;
604  } else
605  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "demuxer does not support additional id3 data, skipping\n");
606  }
607  ff_id3v2_free_extra_meta(&id3v2_extra_meta);
608 
609  if ((ret = avformat_queue_attached_pictures(s)) < 0)
610  goto fail;
611 
612  if (!(s->flags&AVFMT_FLAG_PRIV_OPT) && s->pb && !s->internal->data_offset)
613  s->internal->data_offset = avio_tell(s->pb);
614 
615  s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_remaining_size = RAW_PACKET_BUFFER_SIZE;
616 
617  update_stream_avctx(s);
618 
619  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++)
620  s->streams[i]->internal->orig_codec_id = s->streams[i]->codecpar->codec_id;
621 
622  if (options) {
623  av_dict_free(options);
624  *options = tmp;
625  }
626  *ps = s;
627  return 0;
628 
629 fail:
630  ff_id3v2_free_extra_meta(&id3v2_extra_meta);
631  av_dict_free(&tmp);
632  if (s->pb && !(s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_CUSTOM_IO))
633  avio_closep(&s->pb);
634  avformat_free_context(s);
635  *ps = NULL;
636  return ret;
637 }
638 
639 /*******************************************************/
640 
641 static void force_codec_ids(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st)
642 {
643  switch (st->codecpar->codec_type) {
644  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
645  if (s->video_codec_id)
646  st->codecpar->codec_id = s->video_codec_id;
647  break;
648  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
649  if (s->audio_codec_id)
650  st->codecpar->codec_id = s->audio_codec_id;
651  break;
652  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE:
653  if (s->subtitle_codec_id)
654  st->codecpar->codec_id = s->subtitle_codec_id;
655  break;
656  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
657  if (s->data_codec_id)
658  st->codecpar->codec_id = s->data_codec_id;
659  break;
660  }
661 }
662 
663 static int probe_codec(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st, const AVPacket *pkt)
664 {
665  if (st->request_probe>0) {
666  AVProbeData *pd = &st->probe_data;
667  int end;
668  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "probing stream %d pp:%d\n", st->index, st->probe_packets);
669  --st->probe_packets;
670 
671  if (pkt) {
672  uint8_t *new_buf = av_realloc(pd->buf, pd->buf_size+pkt->size+AVPROBE_PADDING_SIZE);
673  if (!new_buf) {
674  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
675  "Failed to reallocate probe buffer for stream %d\n",
676  st->index);
677  goto no_packet;
678  }
679  pd->buf = new_buf;
680  memcpy(pd->buf + pd->buf_size, pkt->data, pkt->size);
681  pd->buf_size += pkt->size;
682  memset(pd->buf + pd->buf_size, 0, AVPROBE_PADDING_SIZE);
683  } else {
684 no_packet:
685  st->probe_packets = 0;
686  if (!pd->buf_size) {
687  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
688  "nothing to probe for stream %d\n", st->index);
689  }
690  }
691 
692  end= s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_remaining_size <= 0
693  || st->probe_packets<= 0;
694 
695  if (end || av_log2(pd->buf_size) != av_log2(pd->buf_size - pkt->size)) {
696  int score = set_codec_from_probe_data(s, st, pd);
697  if ( (st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE && score > AVPROBE_SCORE_STREAM_RETRY)
698  || end) {
699  pd->buf_size = 0;
700  av_freep(&pd->buf);
701  st->request_probe = -1;
702  if (st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE) {
703  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "probed stream %d\n", st->index);
704  } else
705  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "probed stream %d failed\n", st->index);
706  }
707  force_codec_ids(s, st);
708  }
709  }
710  return 0;
711 }
712 
713 static int update_wrap_reference(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st, int stream_index, AVPacket *pkt)
714 {
715  int64_t ref = pkt->dts;
716  int i, pts_wrap_behavior;
717  int64_t pts_wrap_reference;
718  AVProgram *first_program;
719 
720  if (ref == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
721  ref = pkt->pts;
722  if (st->pts_wrap_reference != AV_NOPTS_VALUE || st->pts_wrap_bits >= 63 || ref == AV_NOPTS_VALUE || !s->correct_ts_overflow)
723  return 0;
724  ref &= (1LL << st->pts_wrap_bits)-1;
725 
726  // reference time stamp should be 60 s before first time stamp
727  pts_wrap_reference = ref - av_rescale(60, st->time_base.den, st->time_base.num);
728  // if first time stamp is not more than 1/8 and 60s before the wrap point, subtract rather than add wrap offset
729  pts_wrap_behavior = (ref < (1LL << st->pts_wrap_bits) - (1LL << st->pts_wrap_bits-3)) ||
730  (ref < (1LL << st->pts_wrap_bits) - av_rescale(60, st->time_base.den, st->time_base.num)) ?
731  AV_PTS_WRAP_ADD_OFFSET : AV_PTS_WRAP_SUB_OFFSET;
732 
733  first_program = av_find_program_from_stream(s, NULL, stream_index);
734 
735  if (!first_program) {
736  int default_stream_index = av_find_default_stream_index(s);
737  if (s->streams[default_stream_index]->pts_wrap_reference == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
738  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
739  if (av_find_program_from_stream(s, NULL, i))
740  continue;
741  s->streams[i]->pts_wrap_reference = pts_wrap_reference;
742  s->streams[i]->pts_wrap_behavior = pts_wrap_behavior;
743  }
744  }
745  else {
746  st->pts_wrap_reference = s->streams[default_stream_index]->pts_wrap_reference;
747  st->pts_wrap_behavior = s->streams[default_stream_index]->pts_wrap_behavior;
748  }
749  }
750  else {
751  AVProgram *program = first_program;
752  while (program) {
753  if (program->pts_wrap_reference != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
754  pts_wrap_reference = program->pts_wrap_reference;
755  pts_wrap_behavior = program->pts_wrap_behavior;
756  break;
757  }
758  program = av_find_program_from_stream(s, program, stream_index);
759  }
760 
761  // update every program with differing pts_wrap_reference
762  program = first_program;
763  while (program) {
764  if (program->pts_wrap_reference != pts_wrap_reference) {
765  for (i = 0; i<program->nb_stream_indexes; i++) {
766  s->streams[program->stream_index[i]]->pts_wrap_reference = pts_wrap_reference;
767  s->streams[program->stream_index[i]]->pts_wrap_behavior = pts_wrap_behavior;
768  }
769 
770  program->pts_wrap_reference = pts_wrap_reference;
771  program->pts_wrap_behavior = pts_wrap_behavior;
772  }
773  program = av_find_program_from_stream(s, program, stream_index);
774  }
775  }
776  return 1;
777 }
778 
779 int ff_read_packet(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
780 {
781  int ret, i, err;
782  AVStream *st;
783 
784  for (;;) {
785  AVPacketList *pktl = s->internal->raw_packet_buffer;
786 
787  if (pktl) {
788  *pkt = pktl->pkt;
789  st = s->streams[pkt->stream_index];
790  if (s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_remaining_size <= 0)
791  if ((err = probe_codec(s, st, NULL)) < 0)
792  return err;
793  if (st->request_probe <= 0) {
794  s->internal->raw_packet_buffer = pktl->next;
795  s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_remaining_size += pkt->size;
796  av_free(pktl);
797  return 0;
798  }
799  }
800 
801  pkt->data = NULL;
802  pkt->size = 0;
803  av_init_packet(pkt);
804  ret = s->iformat->read_packet(s, pkt);
805  if (ret < 0) {
806  /* Some demuxers return FFERROR_REDO when they consume
807  data and discard it (ignored streams, junk, extradata).
808  We must re-call the demuxer to get the real packet. */
809  if (ret == FFERROR_REDO)
810  continue;
811  if (!pktl || ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN))
812  return ret;
813  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
814  st = s->streams[i];
815  if (st->probe_packets || st->request_probe > 0)
816  if ((err = probe_codec(s, st, NULL)) < 0)
817  return err;
818  av_assert0(st->request_probe <= 0);
819  }
820  continue;
821  }
822 
823  if (!pkt->buf) {
824  AVPacket tmp = { 0 };
825  ret = av_packet_ref(&tmp, pkt);
826  if (ret < 0)
827  return ret;
828  *pkt = tmp;
829  }
830 
831  if ((s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_DISCARD_CORRUPT) &&
832  (pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_CORRUPT)) {
833  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
834  "Dropped corrupted packet (stream = %d)\n",
835  pkt->stream_index);
836  av_packet_unref(pkt);
837  continue;
838  }
839 
840  if (pkt->stream_index >= (unsigned)s->nb_streams) {
841  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid stream index %d\n", pkt->stream_index);
842  continue;
843  }
844 
845  st = s->streams[pkt->stream_index];
846 
847  if (update_wrap_reference(s, st, pkt->stream_index, pkt) && st->pts_wrap_behavior == AV_PTS_WRAP_SUB_OFFSET) {
848  // correct first time stamps to negative values
849  if (!is_relative(st->first_dts))
850  st->first_dts = wrap_timestamp(st, st->first_dts);
851  if (!is_relative(st->start_time))
852  st->start_time = wrap_timestamp(st, st->start_time);
853  if (!is_relative(st->cur_dts))
854  st->cur_dts = wrap_timestamp(st, st->cur_dts);
855  }
856 
857  pkt->dts = wrap_timestamp(st, pkt->dts);
858  pkt->pts = wrap_timestamp(st, pkt->pts);
859 
860  force_codec_ids(s, st);
861 
862  /* TODO: audio: time filter; video: frame reordering (pts != dts) */
863  if (s->use_wallclock_as_timestamps)
864  pkt->dts = pkt->pts = av_rescale_q(av_gettime(), AV_TIME_BASE_Q, st->time_base);
865 
866  if (!pktl && st->request_probe <= 0)
867  return ret;
868 
869  err = add_to_pktbuf(&s->internal->raw_packet_buffer, pkt,
870  &s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_end, 0);
871  if (err)
872  return err;
873  s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_remaining_size -= pkt->size;
874 
875  if ((err = probe_codec(s, st, pkt)) < 0)
876  return err;
877  }
878 }
879

881 /**********************************************************/
882 
883 static int determinable_frame_size(AVCodecContext *avctx)
884 {
885  if (/*avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_AAC ||*/
886  avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MP1 ||
887  avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MP2 ||
888  avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MP3/* ||
889  avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_CELT*/)
890  return 1;
891  return 0;
892 }
893 
894 /**
895  * Return the frame duration in seconds. Return 0 if not available.
896  */
897 void ff_compute_frame_duration(AVFormatContext *s, int *pnum, int *pden, AVStream *st,
898  AVCodecParserContext *pc, AVPacket *pkt)
899 {
900  AVRational codec_framerate = s->iformat ? st->internal->avctx->framerate :
901  av_mul_q(av_inv_q(st->internal->avctx->time_base), (AVRational){1, st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame});
902  int frame_size, sample_rate;
903 
904 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
905 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
906  if ((!codec_framerate.den || !codec_framerate.num) && st->codec->time_base.den && st->codec->time_base.num)
907  codec_framerate = av_mul_q(av_inv_q(st->codec->time_base), (AVRational){1, st->codec->ticks_per_frame});
908 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
909 #endif
910 
911  *pnum = 0;
912  *pden = 0;
913  switch (st->codecpar->codec_type) {
914  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
915  if (st->r_frame_rate.num && !pc && s->iformat) {
916  //+: calculate duration from container frame rate
917  *pnum = st->r_frame_rate.den;
918  *pden = st->r_frame_rate.num;
919  } else if (st->time_base.num * 1000LL > st->time_base.den) {
920  //+: if container time_base exceeds 1000, use it
921  *pnum = st->time_base.num;
922  *pden = st->time_base.den;
923  } else if (codec_framerate.den * 1000LL > codec_framerate.num) {
924  //+: use codec time_base
925  av_assert0(st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame);
926  av_reduce(pnum, pden,
927  codec_framerate.den,
928  codec_framerate.num * (int64_t)st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame,
929  INT_MAX);
930 
931  if (pc && pc->repeat_pict) {
932  av_assert0(s->iformat); // this may be wrong for interlaced encoding but its not used for that case
933  av_reduce(pnum, pden,
934  (*pnum) * (1LL + pc->repeat_pict),
935  (*pden),
936  INT_MAX);
937  }
938  /* If this codec can be interlaced or progressive then we need
939  * a parser to compute duration of a packet. Thus if we have
940  * no parser in such case leave duration undefined. */
941  if (st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame > 1 && !pc)
942  *pnum = *pden = 0;
943  }
944  break;
945  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
946  if (st->internal->avctx_inited) {
947  frame_size = av_get_audio_frame_duration(st->internal->avctx, pkt->size);
948  sample_rate = st->internal->avctx->sample_rate;
949  } else {
950  frame_size = av_get_audio_frame_duration2(st->codecpar, pkt->size);
951  sample_rate = st->codecpar->sample_rate;
952  }
953  if (frame_size <= 0 || sample_rate <= 0)
954  break;
955  //+: for audio, duration can be calculated from frame_size and sample_rate
956  *pnum = frame_size;
957  *pden = sample_rate;
958  break;
959  default:
960  break;
961  }
962 }
963 
964 static int is_intra_only(enum AVCodecID id)
965 {
966  const AVCodecDescriptor *d = avcodec_descriptor_get(id);
967  if (!d)
968  return 0;
969  if (d->type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO && !(d->props & AV_CODEC_PROP_INTRA_ONLY))
970  return 0;
971  return 1;
972 }
973 
974 static int has_decode_delay_been_guessed(AVStream *st)
975 {
976  if (st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_H264) return 1;
977  if (!st->info) // if we have left find_stream_info then nb_decoded_frames won't increase anymore for stream copy
978  return 1;
979 #if CONFIG_H264_DECODER
980  if (st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames &&
981  avpriv_h264_has_num_reorder_frames(st->internal->avctx) == st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames)
982  return 1;
983 #endif
984  if (st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames<3)
985  return st->nb_decoded_frames >= 7;
986  else if (st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames<4)
987  return st->nb_decoded_frames >= 18;
988  else
989  return st->nb_decoded_frames >= 20;
990 }
991 
992 static AVPacketList *get_next_pkt(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st, AVPacketList *pktl)
993 {
994  if (pktl->next)
995  return pktl->next;
996  if (pktl == s->internal->packet_buffer_end)
997  return s->internal->parse_queue;
998  return NULL;
999 }
1000 
1001 static int64_t select_from_pts_buffer(AVStream *st, int64_t *pts_buffer, int64_t dts) {
1002  int onein_oneout = st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_H264 &&
1003  st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC;
1004 
1005  if(!onein_oneout) {
1006  int delay = st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames;
1007  int i;
1008 
1009  if (dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1010  int64_t best_score = INT64_MAX;
1011  for (i = 0; i<delay; i++) {
1012  if (st->pts_reorder_error_count[i]) {
1013  int64_t score = st->pts_reorder_error[i] / st->pts_reorder_error_count[i];
1014  if (score < best_score) {
1015  best_score = score;
1016  dts = pts_buffer[i];
1017  }
1018  }
1019  }
1020  } else {
1021  for (i = 0; i<delay; i++) {
1022  if (pts_buffer[i] != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1023  int64_t diff = FFABS(pts_buffer[i] - dts)
1024  + (uint64_t)st->pts_reorder_error[i];
1025  diff = FFMAX(diff, st->pts_reorder_error[i]);
1026  st->pts_reorder_error[i] = diff;
1027  st->pts_reorder_error_count[i]++;
1028  if (st->pts_reorder_error_count[i] > 250) {
1029  st->pts_reorder_error[i] >>= 1;
1030  st->pts_reorder_error_count[i] >>= 1;
1031  }
1032  }
1033  }
1034  }
1035  }
1036 
1037  if (dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1038  dts = pts_buffer[0];
1039 
1040  return dts;
1041 }
1042 
1043 /**
1044  * Updates the dts of packets of a stream in pkt_buffer, by re-ordering the pts
1045  * of the packets in a window.
1046  */
1047 static void update_dts_from_pts(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index,
1048  AVPacketList *pkt_buffer)
1049 {
1050  AVStream *st = s->streams[stream_index];
1051  int delay = st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames;
1052  int i;
1053 
1054  int64_t pts_buffer[MAX_REORDER_DELAY+1];
1055 
1056  for (i = 0; i<MAX_REORDER_DELAY+1; i++)
1057  pts_buffer[i] = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1058 
1059  for (; pkt_buffer; pkt_buffer = get_next_pkt(s, st, pkt_buffer)) {
1060  if (pkt_buffer->pkt.stream_index != stream_index)
1061  continue;
1062 
1063  if (pkt_buffer->pkt.pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && delay <= MAX_REORDER_DELAY) {
1064  pts_buffer[0] = pkt_buffer->pkt.pts;
1065  for (i = 0; i<delay && pts_buffer[i] > pts_buffer[i + 1]; i++)
1066  FFSWAP(int64_t, pts_buffer[i], pts_buffer[i + 1]);
1067 
1068  pkt_buffer->pkt.dts = select_from_pts_buffer(st, pts_buffer, pkt_buffer->pkt.dts);
1069  }
1070  }
1071 }
1072 
1073 static void update_initial_timestamps(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index,
1074  int64_t dts, int64_t pts, AVPacket *pkt)
1075 {
1076  AVStream *st = s->streams[stream_index];
1077  AVPacketList *pktl = s->internal->packet_buffer ? s->internal->packet_buffer : s->internal->parse_queue;
1078  AVPacketList *pktl_it;
1079 
1080  uint64_t shift;
1081 
1082  if (st->first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
1083  dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
1084  st->cur_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
1085  is_relative(dts))
1086  return;
1087 
1088  st->first_dts = dts - (st->cur_dts - RELATIVE_TS_BASE);
1089  st->cur_dts = dts;
1090  shift = (uint64_t)st->first_dts - RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
1091 
1092  if (is_relative(pts))
1093  pts += shift;
1094 
1095  for (pktl_it = pktl; pktl_it; pktl_it = get_next_pkt(s, st, pktl_it)) {
1096  if (pktl_it->pkt.stream_index != stream_index)
1097  continue;
1098  if (is_relative(pktl_it->pkt.pts))
1099  pktl_it->pkt.pts += shift;
1100 
1101  if (is_relative(pktl_it->pkt.dts))
1102  pktl_it->pkt.dts += shift;
1103 
1104  if (st->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE && pktl_it->pkt.pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1105  st->start_time = pktl_it->pkt.pts;
1106  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO && st->codecpar->sample_rate)
1107  st->start_time += av_rescale_q(st->skip_samples, (AVRational){1, st->codecpar->sample_rate}, st->time_base);
1108  }
1109  }
1110 
1111  if (has_decode_delay_been_guessed(st)) {
1112  update_dts_from_pts(s, stream_index, pktl);
1113  }
1114 
1115  if (st->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1116  st->start_time = pts;
1117  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO && st->codecpar->sample_rate)
1118  st->start_time += av_rescale_q(st->skip_samples, (AVRational){1, st->codecpar->sample_rate}, st->time_base);
1119  }
1120 }
1121 
1122 static void update_initial_durations(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
1123  int stream_index, int duration)
1124 {
1125  AVPacketList *pktl = s->internal->packet_buffer ? s->internal->packet_buffer : s->internal->parse_queue;
1126  int64_t cur_dts = RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
1127 
1128  if (st->first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1129  if (st->update_initial_durations_done)
1130  return;
1131  st->update_initial_durations_done = 1;
1132  cur_dts = st->first_dts;
1133  for (; pktl; pktl = get_next_pkt(s, st, pktl)) {
1134  if (pktl->pkt.stream_index == stream_index) {
1135  if (pktl->pkt.pts != pktl->pkt.dts ||
1136  pktl->pkt.dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
1137  pktl->pkt.duration)
1138  break;
1139  cur_dts -= duration;
1140  }
1141  }
1142  if (pktl && pktl->pkt.dts != st->first_dts) {
1143  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "first_dts %s not matching first dts %s (pts %s, duration %"PRId64") in the queue\n",
1144  av_ts2str(st->first_dts), av_ts2str(pktl->pkt.dts), av_ts2str(pktl->pkt.pts), pktl->pkt.duration);
1145  return;
1146  }
1147  if (!pktl) {
1148  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "first_dts %s but no packet with dts in the queue\n", av_ts2str(st->first_dts));
1149  return;
1150  }
1151  pktl = s->internal->packet_buffer ? s->internal->packet_buffer : s->internal->parse_queue;
1152  st->first_dts = cur_dts;
1153  } else if (st->cur_dts != RELATIVE_TS_BASE)
1154  return;
1155 
1156  for (; pktl; pktl = get_next_pkt(s, st, pktl)) {
1157  if (pktl->pkt.stream_index != stream_index)
1158  continue;
1159  if (pktl->pkt.pts == pktl->pkt.dts &&
1160  (pktl->pkt.dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE || pktl->pkt.dts == st->first_dts) &&
1161  !pktl->pkt.duration) {
1162  pktl->pkt.dts = cur_dts;
1163  if (!st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames)
1164  pktl->pkt.pts = cur_dts;
1165 // if (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)
1166  pktl->pkt.duration = duration;
1167  } else
1168  break;
1169  cur_dts = pktl->pkt.dts + pktl->pkt.duration;
1170  }
1171  if (!pktl)
1172  st->cur_dts = cur_dts;
1173 }
1174 
1175 static void compute_pkt_fields(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
1176  AVCodecParserContext *pc, AVPacket *pkt,
1177  int64_t next_dts, int64_t next_pts)
1178 {
1179  int num, den, presentation_delayed, delay, i;
1180  int64_t offset;
1181  AVRational duration;
1182  int onein_oneout = st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_H264 &&
1183  st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC;
1184 
1185  if (s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOFILLIN)
1186  return;
1187 
1188  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO && pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1189  if (pkt->dts == pkt->pts && st->last_dts_for_order_check != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1190  if (st->last_dts_for_order_check <= pkt->dts) {
1191  st->dts_ordered++;
1192  } else {
1193  av_log(s, st->dts_misordered ? AV_LOG_DEBUG : AV_LOG_WARNING,
1194  "DTS %"PRIi64" < %"PRIi64" out of order\n",
1195  pkt->dts,
1196  st->last_dts_for_order_check);
1197  st->dts_misordered++;
1198  }
1199  if (st->dts_ordered + st->dts_misordered > 250) {
1200  st->dts_ordered >>= 1;
1201  st->dts_misordered >>= 1;
1202  }
1203  }
1204 
1205  st->last_dts_for_order_check = pkt->dts;
1206  if (st->dts_ordered < 8*st->dts_misordered && pkt->dts == pkt->pts)
1207  pkt->dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1208  }
1209 
1210  if ((s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_IGNDTS) && pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1211  pkt->dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1212 
1213  if (pc && pc->pict_type == AV_PICTURE_TYPE_B
1214  && !st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames)
1215  //FIXME Set low_delay = 0 when has_b_frames = 1
1216  st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames = 1;
1217 
1218  /* do we have a video B-frame ? */
1219  delay = st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames;
1220  presentation_delayed = 0;
1221 
1222  /* XXX: need has_b_frame, but cannot get it if the codec is
1223  * not initialized */
1224  if (delay &&
1225  pc && pc->pict_type != AV_PICTURE_TYPE_B)
1226  presentation_delayed = 1;
1227 
1228  if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
1229  st->pts_wrap_bits < 63 &&
1230  pkt->dts - (1LL << (st->pts_wrap_bits - 1)) > pkt->pts) {
1231  if (is_relative(st->cur_dts) || pkt->dts - (1LL<<(st->pts_wrap_bits - 1)) > st->cur_dts) {
1232  pkt->dts -= 1LL << st->pts_wrap_bits;
1233  } else
1234  pkt->pts += 1LL << st->pts_wrap_bits;
1235  }
1236 
1237  /* Some MPEG-2 in MPEG-PS lack dts (issue #171 / input_file.mpg).
1238  * We take the conservative approach and discard both.
1239  * Note: If this is misbehaving for an H.264 file, then possibly
1240  * presentation_delayed is not set correctly. */
1241  if (delay == 1 && pkt->dts == pkt->pts &&
1242  pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && presentation_delayed) {
1243  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "invalid dts/pts combination %"PRIi64"\n", pkt->dts);
1244  if ( strcmp(s->iformat->name, "mov,mp4,m4a,3gp,3g2,mj2")
1245  && strcmp(s->iformat->name, "flv")) // otherwise we discard correct timestamps for vc1-wmapro.ism
1246  pkt->dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1247  }
1248 
1249  duration = av_mul_q((AVRational) {pkt->duration, 1}, st->time_base);
1250  if (pkt->duration == 0) {
1251  ff_compute_frame_duration(s, &num, &den, st, pc, pkt);
1252  if (den && num) {
1253  duration = (AVRational) {num, den};
1254  pkt->duration = av_rescale_rnd(1,
1255  num * (int64_t) st->time_base.den,
1256  den * (int64_t) st->time_base.num,
1257  AV_ROUND_DOWN);
1258  }
1259  }
1260 
1261  if (pkt->duration != 0 && (s->internal->packet_buffer || s->internal->parse_queue))
1262  update_initial_durations(s, st, pkt->stream_index, pkt->duration);
1263 
1264  /* Correct timestamps with byte offset if demuxers only have timestamps
1265  * on packet boundaries */
1266  if (pc && st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_TIMESTAMPS && pkt->size) {
1267  /* this will estimate bitrate based on this frame's duration and size */
1268  offset = av_rescale(pc->offset, pkt->duration, pkt->size);
1269  if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1270  pkt->pts += offset;
1271  if (pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1272  pkt->dts += offset;
1273  }
1274 
1275  /* This may be redundant, but it should not hurt. */
1276  if (pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
1277  pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
1278  pkt->pts > pkt->dts)
1279  presentation_delayed = 1;
1280 
1281  if (s->debug & FF_FDEBUG_TS)
1282  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE,
1283  "IN delayed:%d pts:%s, dts:%s cur_dts:%s st:%d pc:%p duration:%"PRId64" delay:%d onein_oneout:%d\n",
1284  presentation_delayed, av_ts2str(pkt->pts), av_ts2str(pkt->dts), av_ts2str(st->cur_dts),
1285  pkt->stream_index, pc, pkt->duration, delay, onein_oneout);
1286 
1287  /* Interpolate PTS and DTS if they are not present. We skip H264
1288  * currently because delay and has_b_frames are not reliably set. */
1289  if ((delay == 0 || (delay == 1 && pc)) &&
1290  onein_oneout) {
1291  if (presentation_delayed) {
1292  /* DTS = decompression timestamp */
1293  /* PTS = presentation timestamp */
1294  if (pkt->dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1295  pkt->dts = st->last_IP_pts;
1296  update_initial_timestamps(s, pkt->stream_index, pkt->dts, pkt->pts, pkt);
1297  if (pkt->dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1298  pkt->dts = st->cur_dts;
1299 
1300  /* This is tricky: the dts must be incremented by the duration
1301  * of the frame we are displaying, i.e. the last I- or P-frame. */
1302  if (st->last_IP_duration == 0)
1303  st->last_IP_duration = pkt->duration;
1304  if (pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1305  st->cur_dts = pkt->dts + st->last_IP_duration;
1306  if (pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
1307  pkt->pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
1308  st->last_IP_duration > 0 &&
1309  ((uint64_t)st->cur_dts - (uint64_t)next_dts + 1) <= 2 &&
1310  next_dts != next_pts &&
1311  next_pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1312  pkt->pts = next_dts;
1313 
1314  st->last_IP_duration = pkt->duration;
1315  st->last_IP_pts = pkt->pts;
1316  /* Cannot compute PTS if not present (we can compute it only
1317  * by knowing the future. */
1318  } else if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
1319  pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
1320  pkt->duration ) {
1321 
1322  /* presentation is not delayed : PTS and DTS are the same */
1323  if (pkt->pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1324  pkt->pts = pkt->dts;
1325  update_initial_timestamps(s, pkt->stream_index, pkt->pts,
1326  pkt->pts, pkt);
1327  if (pkt->pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1328  pkt->pts = st->cur_dts;
1329  pkt->dts = pkt->pts;
1330  if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1331  st->cur_dts = av_add_stable(st->time_base, pkt->pts, duration, 1);
1332  }
1333  }
1334 
1335  if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && delay <= MAX_REORDER_DELAY) {
1336  st->pts_buffer[0] = pkt->pts;
1337  for (i = 0; i<delay && st->pts_buffer[i] > st->pts_buffer[i + 1]; i++)
1338  FFSWAP(int64_t, st->pts_buffer[i], st->pts_buffer[i + 1]);
1339 
1340  if(has_decode_delay_been_guessed(st))
1341  pkt->dts = select_from_pts_buffer(st, st->pts_buffer, pkt->dts);
1342  }
1343  // We skipped it above so we try here.
1344  if (!onein_oneout)
1345  // This should happen on the first packet
1346  update_initial_timestamps(s, pkt->stream_index, pkt->dts, pkt->pts, pkt);
1347  if (pkt->dts > st->cur_dts)
1348  st->cur_dts = pkt->dts;
1349 
1350  if (s->debug & FF_FDEBUG_TS)
1351  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE, "OUTdelayed:%d/%d pts:%s, dts:%s cur_dts:%s\n",
1352  presentation_delayed, delay, av_ts2str(pkt->pts), av_ts2str(pkt->dts), av_ts2str(st->cur_dts));
1353 
1354  /* update flags */
1355  if (is_intra_only(st->codecpar->codec_id))
1356  pkt->flags |= AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY;
1357 #if FF_API_CONVERGENCE_DURATION
1358 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
1359  if (pc)
1360  pkt->convergence_duration = pc->convergence_duration;
1361 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
1362 #endif
1363 }
1364 
1365 static void free_packet_buffer(AVPacketList **pkt_buf, AVPacketList **pkt_buf_end)
1366 {
1367  while (*pkt_buf) {
1368  AVPacketList *pktl = *pkt_buf;
1369  *pkt_buf = pktl->next;
1370  av_packet_unref(&pktl->pkt);
1371  av_freep(&pktl);
1372  }
1373  *pkt_buf_end = NULL;
1374 }
1375 
1376 /**
1377  * Parse a packet, add all split parts to parse_queue.
1378  *
1379  * @param pkt Packet to parse, NULL when flushing the parser at end of stream.
1380  */
1381 static int parse_packet(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt, int stream_index)
1382 {
1383  AVPacket out_pkt = { 0 }, flush_pkt = { 0 };
1384  AVStream *st = s->streams[stream_index];
1385  uint8_t *data = pkt ? pkt->data : NULL;
1386  int size = pkt ? pkt->size : 0;
1387  int ret = 0, got_output = 0;
1388 
1389  if (!pkt) {
1390  av_init_packet(&flush_pkt);
1391  pkt = &flush_pkt;
1392  got_output = 1;
1393  } else if (!size && st->parser->flags & PARSER_FLAG_COMPLETE_FRAMES) {
1394  // preserve 0-size sync packets
1395  compute_pkt_fields(s, st, st->parser, pkt, AV_NOPTS_VALUE, AV_NOPTS_VALUE);
1396  }
1397 
1398  while (size > 0 || (pkt == &flush_pkt && got_output)) {
1399  int len;
1400  int64_t next_pts = pkt->pts;
1401  int64_t next_dts = pkt->dts;
1402 
1403  av_init_packet(&out_pkt);
1404  len = av_parser_parse2(st->parser, st->internal->avctx,
1405  &out_pkt.data, &out_pkt.size, data, size,
1406  pkt->pts, pkt->dts, pkt->pos);
1407 
1408  pkt->pts = pkt->dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1409  pkt->pos = -1;
1410  /* increment read pointer */
1411  data += len;
1412  size -= len;
1413 
1414  got_output = !!out_pkt.size;
1415 
1416  if (!out_pkt.size)
1417  continue;
1418 
1419  if (pkt->side_data) {
1420  out_pkt.side_data = pkt->side_data;
1421  out_pkt.side_data_elems = pkt->side_data_elems;
1422  pkt->side_data = NULL;
1423  pkt->side_data_elems = 0;
1424  }
1425 
1426  /* set the duration */
1427  out_pkt.duration = (st->parser->flags & PARSER_FLAG_COMPLETE_FRAMES) ? pkt->duration : 0;
1428  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
1429  if (st->internal->avctx->sample_rate > 0) {
1430  out_pkt.duration =
1431  av_rescale_q_rnd(st->parser->duration,
1432  (AVRational) { 1, st->internal->avctx->sample_rate },
1433  st->time_base,
1434  AV_ROUND_DOWN);
1435  }
1436  }
1437 
1438  out_pkt.stream_index = st->index;
1439  out_pkt.pts = st->parser->pts;
1440  out_pkt.dts = st->parser->dts;
1441  out_pkt.pos = st->parser->pos;
1442 
1443  if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_FULL_RAW)
1444  out_pkt.pos = st->parser->frame_offset;
1445 
1446  if (st->parser->key_frame == 1 ||
1447  (st->parser->key_frame == -1 &&
1448  st->parser->pict_type == AV_PICTURE_TYPE_I))
1449  out_pkt.flags |= AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY;
1450 
1451  if (st->parser->key_frame == -1 && st->parser->pict_type ==AV_PICTURE_TYPE_NONE && (pkt->flags&AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY))
1452  out_pkt.flags |= AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY;
1453 
1454  compute_pkt_fields(s, st, st->parser, &out_pkt, next_dts, next_pts);
1455 
1456  ret = add_to_pktbuf(&s->internal->parse_queue, &out_pkt,
1457  &s->internal->parse_queue_end, 1);
1458  av_packet_unref(&out_pkt);
1459  if (ret < 0)
1460  goto fail;
1461  }
1462 
1463  /* end of the stream => close and free the parser */
1464  if (pkt == &flush_pkt) {
1465  av_parser_close(st->parser);
1466  st->parser = NULL;
1467  }
1468 
1469 fail:
1470  av_packet_unref(pkt);
1471  return ret;
1472 }
1473 
1474 static int read_from_packet_buffer(AVPacketList **pkt_buffer,
1475  AVPacketList **pkt_buffer_end,
1476  AVPacket *pkt)
1477 {
1478  AVPacketList *pktl;
1479  av_assert0(*pkt_buffer);
1480  pktl = *pkt_buffer;
1481  *pkt = pktl->pkt;
1482  *pkt_buffer = pktl->next;
1483  if (!pktl->next)
1484  *pkt_buffer_end = NULL;
1485  av_freep(&pktl);
1486  return 0;
1487 }
1488 
1489 static int64_t ts_to_samples(AVStream *st, int64_t ts)
1490 {
1491  return av_rescale(ts, st->time_base.num * st->codecpar->sample_rate, st->time_base.den);
1492 }
1493 
1494 static int read_frame_internal(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
1495 {
1496  int ret = 0, i, got_packet = 0;
1497  AVDictionary *metadata = NULL;
1498 
1499  av_init_packet(pkt);
1500 
1501  while (!got_packet && !s->internal->parse_queue) {
1502  AVStream *st;
1503  AVPacket cur_pkt;
1504 
1505  /* read next packet */
1506  ret = ff_read_packet(s, &cur_pkt);
1507  if (ret < 0) {
1508  if (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN))
1509  return ret;
1510  /* flush the parsers */
1511  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
1512  st = s->streams[i];
1513  if (st->parser && st->need_parsing)
1514  parse_packet(s, NULL, st->index);
1515  }
1516  /* all remaining packets are now in parse_queue =>
1517  * really terminate parsing */
1518  break;
1519  }
1520  ret = 0;
1521  st = s->streams[cur_pkt.stream_index];
1522 
1523  /* update context if required */
1524  if (st->internal->need_context_update) {
1525  if (avcodec_is_open(st->internal->avctx)) {
1526  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "Demuxer context update while decoder is open, closing and trying to re-open\n");
1527  avcodec_close(st->internal->avctx);
1528  st->info->found_decoder = 0;
1529  }
1530 
1531  /* close parser, because it depends on the codec */
1532  if (st->parser && st->internal->avctx->codec_id != st->codecpar->codec_id) {
1533  av_parser_close(st->parser);
1534  st->parser = NULL;
1535  }
1536 
1537  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->internal->avctx, st->codecpar);
1538  if (ret < 0)
1539  return ret;
1540 
1541 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
1542 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
1543  /* update deprecated public codec context */
1544  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->codec, st->codecpar);
1545  if (ret < 0)
1546  return ret;
1547 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
1548 #endif
1549 
1550  st->internal->need_context_update = 0;
1551  }
1552 
1553  if (cur_pkt.pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
1554  cur_pkt.dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
1555  cur_pkt.pts < cur_pkt.dts) {
1556  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING,
1557  "Invalid timestamps stream=%d, pts=%s, dts=%s, size=%d\n",
1558  cur_pkt.stream_index,
1559  av_ts2str(cur_pkt.pts),
1560  av_ts2str(cur_pkt.dts),
1561  cur_pkt.size);
1562  }
1563  if (s->debug & FF_FDEBUG_TS)
1564  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
1565  "ff_read_packet stream=%d, pts=%s, dts=%s, size=%d, duration=%"PRId64", flags=%d\n",
1566  cur_pkt.stream_index,
1567  av_ts2str(cur_pkt.pts),
1568  av_ts2str(cur_pkt.dts),
1569  cur_pkt.size, cur_pkt.duration, cur_pkt.flags);
1570 
1571  if (st->need_parsing && !st->parser && !(s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOPARSE)) {
1572  st->parser = av_parser_init(st->codecpar->codec_id);
1573  if (!st->parser) {
1574  av_log(s, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "parser not found for codec "
1575  "%s, packets or times may be invalid.\n",
1576  avcodec_get_name(st->codecpar->codec_id));
1577  /* no parser available: just output the raw packets */
1578  st->need_parsing = AVSTREAM_PARSE_NONE;
1579  } else if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_HEADERS)
1580  st->parser->flags |= PARSER_FLAG_COMPLETE_FRAMES;
1581  else if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_FULL_ONCE)
1582  st->parser->flags |= PARSER_FLAG_ONCE;
1583  else if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_FULL_RAW)
1584  st->parser->flags |= PARSER_FLAG_USE_CODEC_TS;
1585  }
1586 
1587  if (!st->need_parsing || !st->parser) {
1588  /* no parsing needed: we just output the packet as is */
1589  *pkt = cur_pkt;
1590  compute_pkt_fields(s, st, NULL, pkt, AV_NOPTS_VALUE, AV_NOPTS_VALUE);
1591  if ((s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_GENERIC_INDEX) &&
1592  (pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY) && pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1593  ff_reduce_index(s, st->index);
1594  av_add_index_entry(st, pkt->pos, pkt->dts,
1595  0, 0, AVINDEX_KEYFRAME);
1596  }
1597  got_packet = 1;
1598  } else if (st->discard < AVDISCARD_ALL) {
1599  if ((ret = parse_packet(s, &cur_pkt, cur_pkt.stream_index)) < 0)
1600  return ret;
1601  st->codecpar->sample_rate = st->internal->avctx->sample_rate;
1602  st->codecpar->bit_rate = st->internal->avctx->bit_rate;
1603  st->codecpar->channels = st->internal->avctx->channels;
1604  st->codecpar->channel_layout = st->internal->avctx->channel_layout;
1605  st->codecpar->codec_id = st->internal->avctx->codec_id;
1606  } else {
1607  /* free packet */
1608  av_packet_unref(&cur_pkt);
1609  }
1610  if (pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY)
1611  st->skip_to_keyframe = 0;
1612  if (st->skip_to_keyframe) {
1613  av_packet_unref(&cur_pkt);
1614  if (got_packet) {
1615  *pkt = cur_pkt;
1616  }
1617  got_packet = 0;
1618  }
1619  }
1620 
1621  if (!got_packet && s->internal->parse_queue)
1622  ret = read_from_packet_buffer(&s->internal->parse_queue, &s->internal->parse_queue_end, pkt);
1623 
1624  if (ret >= 0) {
1625  AVStream *st = s->streams[pkt->stream_index];
1626  int discard_padding = 0;
1627  if (st->first_discard_sample && pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1628  int64_t pts = pkt->pts - (is_relative(pkt->pts) ? RELATIVE_TS_BASE : 0);
1629  int64_t sample = ts_to_samples(st, pts);
1630  int duration = ts_to_samples(st, pkt->duration);
1631  int64_t end_sample = sample + duration;
1632  if (duration > 0 && end_sample >= st->first_discard_sample &&
1633  sample < st->last_discard_sample)
1634  discard_padding = FFMIN(end_sample - st->first_discard_sample, duration);
1635  }
1636  if (st->start_skip_samples && (pkt->pts == 0 || pkt->pts == RELATIVE_TS_BASE))
1637  st->skip_samples = st->start_skip_samples;
1638  if (st->skip_samples || discard_padding) {
1639  uint8_t *p = av_packet_new_side_data(pkt, AV_PKT_DATA_SKIP_SAMPLES, 10);
1640  if (p) {
1641  AV_WL32(p, st->skip_samples);
1642  AV_WL32(p + 4, discard_padding);
1643  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "demuxer injecting skip %d / discard %d\n", st->skip_samples, discard_padding);
1644  }
1645  st->skip_samples = 0;
1646  }
1647 
1648  if (st->inject_global_side_data) {
1649  for (i = 0; i < st->nb_side_data; i++) {
1650  AVPacketSideData *src_sd = &st->side_data[i];
1651  uint8_t *dst_data;
1652 
1653  if (av_packet_get_side_data(pkt, src_sd->type, NULL))
1654  continue;
1655 
1656  dst_data = av_packet_new_side_data(pkt, src_sd->type, src_sd->size);
1657  if (!dst_data) {
1658  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "Could not inject global side data\n");
1659  continue;
1660  }
1661 
1662  memcpy(dst_data, src_sd->data, src_sd->size);
1663  }
1664  st->inject_global_side_data = 0;
1665  }
1666 
1667  if (!(s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_KEEP_SIDE_DATA))
1668  av_packet_merge_side_data(pkt);
1669  }
1670 
1671  av_opt_get_dict_val(s, "metadata", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN, &metadata);
1672  if (metadata) {
1673  s->event_flags |= AVFMT_EVENT_FLAG_METADATA_UPDATED;
1674  av_dict_copy(&s->metadata, metadata, 0);
1675  av_dict_free(&metadata);
1676  av_opt_set_dict_val(s, "metadata", NULL, AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
1677  }
1678 
1679 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
1680  update_stream_avctx(s);
1681 #endif
1682 
1683  if (s->debug & FF_FDEBUG_TS)
1684  av_log(s, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
1685  "read_frame_internal stream=%d, pts=%s, dts=%s, "
1686  "size=%d, duration=%"PRId64", flags=%d\n",
1687  pkt->stream_index,
1688  av_ts2str(pkt->pts),
1689  av_ts2str(pkt->dts),
1690  pkt->size, pkt->duration, pkt->flags);
1691 
1692  return ret;
1693 }
1694 
1695 int av_read_frame(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
1696 {
1697  const int genpts = s->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_GENPTS;
1698  int eof = 0;
1699  int ret;
1700  AVStream *st;
1701 
1702  if (!genpts) {
1703  ret = s->internal->packet_buffer
1704  ? read_from_packet_buffer(&s->internal->packet_buffer,
1705  &s->internal->packet_buffer_end, pkt)
1706  : read_frame_internal(s, pkt);
1707  if (ret < 0)
1708  return ret;
1709  goto return_packet;
1710  }
1711 
1712  for (;;) {
1713  AVPacketList *pktl = s->internal->packet_buffer;
1714 
1715  if (pktl) {
1716  AVPacket *next_pkt = &pktl->pkt;
1717 
1718  if (next_pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1719  int wrap_bits = s->streams[next_pkt->stream_index]->pts_wrap_bits;
1720  // last dts seen for this stream. if any of packets following
1721  // current one had no dts, we will set this to AV_NOPTS_VALUE.
1722  int64_t last_dts = next_pkt->dts;
1723  while (pktl && next_pkt->pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1724  if (pktl->pkt.stream_index == next_pkt->stream_index &&
1725  (av_compare_mod(next_pkt->dts, pktl->pkt.dts, 2LL << (wrap_bits - 1)) < 0)) {
1726  if (av_compare_mod(pktl->pkt.pts, pktl->pkt.dts, 2LL << (wrap_bits - 1))) {
1727  // not B-frame
1728  next_pkt->pts = pktl->pkt.dts;
1729  }
1730  if (last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1731  // Once last dts was set to AV_NOPTS_VALUE, we don't change it.
1732  last_dts = pktl->pkt.dts;
1733  }
1734  }
1735  pktl = pktl->next;
1736  }
1737  if (eof && next_pkt->pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE && last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
1738  // Fixing the last reference frame had none pts issue (For MXF etc).
1739  // We only do this when
1740  // 1. eof.
1741  // 2. we are not able to resolve a pts value for current packet.
1742  // 3. the packets for this stream at the end of the files had valid dts.
1743  next_pkt->pts = last_dts + next_pkt->duration;
1744  }
1745  pktl = s->internal->packet_buffer;
1746  }
1747 
1748  /* read packet from packet buffer, if there is data */
1749  st = s->streams[next_pkt->stream_index];
1750  if (!(next_pkt->pts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE && st->discard < AVDISCARD_ALL &&
1751  next_pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && !eof)) {
1752  ret = read_from_packet_buffer(&s->internal->packet_buffer,
1753  &s->internal->packet_buffer_end, pkt);
1754  goto return_packet;
1755  }
1756  }
1757 
1758  ret = read_frame_internal(s, pkt);
1759  if (ret < 0) {
1760  if (pktl && ret != AVERROR(EAGAIN)) {
1761  eof = 1;
1762  continue;
1763  } else
1764  return ret;
1765  }
1766 
1767  ret = add_to_pktbuf(&s->internal->packet_buffer, pkt,
1768  &s->internal->packet_buffer_end, 1);
1769  av_packet_unref(pkt);
1770  if (ret < 0)
1771  return ret;
1772  }
1773 
1774 return_packet:
1775 
1776  st = s->streams[pkt->stream_index];
1777  if ((s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_GENERIC_INDEX) && pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY) {
1778  ff_reduce_index(s, st->index);
1779  av_add_index_entry(st, pkt->pos, pkt->dts, 0, 0, AVINDEX_KEYFRAME);
1780  }
1781 
1782  if (is_relative(pkt->dts))
1783  pkt->dts -= RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
1784  if (is_relative(pkt->pts))
1785  pkt->pts -= RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
1786 
1787  return ret;
1788 }
1789 
1790 /* XXX: suppress the packet queue */
1791 static void flush_packet_queue(AVFormatContext *s)
1792 {
1793  if (!s->internal)
1794  return;
1795  free_packet_buffer(&s->internal->parse_queue, &s->internal->parse_queue_end);
1796  free_packet_buffer(&s->internal->packet_buffer, &s->internal->packet_buffer_end);
1797  free_packet_buffer(&s->internal->raw_packet_buffer, &s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_end);
1798 
1799  s->internal->raw_packet_buffer_remaining_size = RAW_PACKET_BUFFER_SIZE;
1800 }
1801 
1802 /*******************************************************/
1803 /* seek support */
1804 
1805 int av_find_default_stream_index(AVFormatContext *s)
1806 {
1807  int i;
1808  AVStream *st;
1809  int best_stream = 0;
1810  int best_score = INT_MIN;
1811 
1812  if (s->nb_streams <= 0)
1813  return -1;
1814  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
1815  int score = 0;
1816  st = s->streams[i];
1817  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
1818  if (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC)
1819  score -= 400;
1820  if (st->codecpar->width && st->codecpar->height)
1821  score += 50;
1822  score+= 25;
1823  }
1824  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
1825  if (st->codecpar->sample_rate)
1826  score += 50;
1827  }
1828  if (st->codec_info_nb_frames)
1829  score += 12;
1830 
1831  if (st->discard != AVDISCARD_ALL)
1832  score += 200;
1833 
1834  if (score > best_score) {
1835  best_score = score;
1836  best_stream = i;
1837  }
1838  }
1839  return best_stream;
1840 }
1841 
1842 /** Flush the frame reader. */
1843 void ff_read_frame_flush(AVFormatContext *s)
1844 {
1845  AVStream *st;
1846  int i, j;
1847 
1848  flush_packet_queue(s);
1849 
1850  /* Reset read state for each stream. */
1851  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
1852  st = s->streams[i];
1853 
1854  if (st->parser) {
1855  av_parser_close(st->parser);
1856  st->parser = NULL;
1857  }
1858  st->last_IP_pts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1859  st->last_dts_for_order_check = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1860  if (st->first_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1861  st->cur_dts = RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
1862  else
1863  /* We set the current DTS to an unspecified origin. */
1864  st->cur_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1865 
1866  st->probe_packets = MAX_PROBE_PACKETS;
1867 
1868  for (j = 0; j < MAX_REORDER_DELAY + 1; j++)
1869  st->pts_buffer[j] = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
1870 
1871  if (s->internal->inject_global_side_data)
1872  st->inject_global_side_data = 1;
1873 
1874  st->skip_samples = 0;
1875  }
1876 }
1877 
1878 void ff_update_cur_dts(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *ref_st, int64_t timestamp)
1879 {
1880  int i;
1881 
1882  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
1883  AVStream *st = s->streams[i];
1884 
1885  st->cur_dts =
1886  av_rescale(timestamp,
1887  st->time_base.den * (int64_t) ref_st->time_base.num,
1888  st->time_base.num * (int64_t) ref_st->time_base.den);
1889  }
1890 }
1891 
1892 void ff_reduce_index(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index)
1893 {
1894  AVStream *st = s->streams[stream_index];
1895  unsigned int max_entries = s->max_index_size / sizeof(AVIndexEntry);
1896 
1897  if ((unsigned) st->nb_index_entries >= max_entries) {
1898  int i;
1899  for (i = 0; 2 * i < st->nb_index_entries; i++)
1900  st->index_entries[i] = st->index_entries[2 * i];
1901  st->nb_index_entries = i;
1902  }
1903 }
1904 
1905 int ff_add_index_entry(AVIndexEntry **index_entries,
1906  int *nb_index_entries,
1907  unsigned int *index_entries_allocated_size,
1908  int64_t pos, int64_t timestamp,
1909  int size, int distance, int flags)
1910 {
1911  AVIndexEntry *entries, *ie;
1912  int index;
1913 
1914  if ((unsigned) *nb_index_entries + 1 >= UINT_MAX / sizeof(AVIndexEntry))
1915  return -1;
1916 
1917  if (timestamp == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
1918  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
1919 
1920  if (size < 0 || size > 0x3FFFFFFF)
1921  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
1922 
1923  if (is_relative(timestamp)) //FIXME this maintains previous behavior but we should shift by the correct offset once known
1924  timestamp -= RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
1925 
1926  entries = av_fast_realloc(*index_entries,
1927  index_entries_allocated_size,
1928  (*nb_index_entries + 1) *
1929  sizeof(AVIndexEntry));
1930  if (!entries)
1931  return -1;
1932 
1933  *index_entries = entries;
1934 
1935  index = ff_index_search_timestamp(*index_entries, *nb_index_entries,
1936  timestamp, AVSEEK_FLAG_ANY);
1937 
1938  if (index < 0) {
1939  index = (*nb_index_entries)++;
1940  ie = &entries[index];
1941  av_assert0(index == 0 || ie[-1].timestamp < timestamp);
1942  } else {
1943  ie = &entries[index];
1944  if (ie->timestamp != timestamp) {
1945  if (ie->timestamp <= timestamp)
1946  return -1;
1947  memmove(entries + index + 1, entries + index,
1948  sizeof(AVIndexEntry) * (*nb_index_entries - index));
1949  (*nb_index_entries)++;
1950  } else if (ie->pos == pos && distance < ie->min_distance)
1951  // do not reduce the distance
1952  distance = ie->min_distance;
1953  }
1954 
1955  ie->pos = pos;
1956  ie->timestamp = timestamp;
1957  ie->min_distance = distance;
1958  ie->size = size;
1959  ie->flags = flags;
1960 
1961  return index;
1962 }
1963 
1964 int av_add_index_entry(AVStream *st, int64_t pos, int64_t timestamp,
1965  int size, int distance, int flags)
1966 {
1967  timestamp = wrap_timestamp(st, timestamp);
1968  return ff_add_index_entry(&st->index_entries, &st->nb_index_entries,
1969  &st->index_entries_allocated_size, pos,
1970  timestamp, size, distance, flags);
1971 }
1972 
1973 int ff_index_search_timestamp(const AVIndexEntry *entries, int nb_entries,
1974  int64_t wanted_timestamp, int flags)
1975 {
1976  int a, b, m;
1977  int64_t timestamp;
1978 
1979  a = -1;
1980  b = nb_entries;
1981 
1982  // Optimize appending index entries at the end.
1983  if (b && entries[b - 1].timestamp < wanted_timestamp)
1984  a = b - 1;
1985 
1986  while (b - a > 1) {
1987  m = (a + b) >> 1;
1988 
1989  // Search for the next non-discarded packet.
1990  while ((entries[m].flags & AVINDEX_DISCARD_FRAME) && m < b && m < nb_entries - 1) {
1991  m++;
1992  if (m == b && entries[m].timestamp >= wanted_timestamp) {
1993  m = b - 1;
1994  break;
1995  }
1996  }
1997 
1998  timestamp = entries[m].timestamp;
1999  if (timestamp >= wanted_timestamp)
2000  b = m;
2001  if (timestamp <= wanted_timestamp)
2002  a = m;
2003  }
2004  m = (flags & AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD) ? a : b;
2005 
2006  if (!(flags & AVSEEK_FLAG_ANY))
2007  while (m >= 0 && m < nb_entries &&
2008  !(entries[m].flags & AVINDEX_KEYFRAME))
2009  m += (flags & AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD) ? -1 : 1;
2010 
2011  if (m == nb_entries)
2012  return -1;
2013  return m;
2014 }
2015 
2016 void ff_configure_buffers_for_index(AVFormatContext *s, int64_t time_tolerance)
2017 {
2018  int ist1, ist2;
2019  int64_t pos_delta = 0;
2020  int64_t skip = 0;
2021  //We could use URLProtocol flags here but as many user applications do not use URLProtocols this would be unreliable
2022  const char *proto = avio_find_protocol_name(s->filename);
2023 
2024  if (!proto) {
2025  av_log(s, AV_LOG_INFO,
2026  "Protocol name not provided, cannot determine if input is local or "
2027  "a network protocol, buffers and access patterns cannot be configured "
2028  "optimally without knowing the protocol\n");
2029  }
2030 
2031  if (proto && !(strcmp(proto, "file") && strcmp(proto, "pipe") && strcmp(proto, "cache")))
2032  return;
2033 
2034  for (ist1 = 0; ist1 < s->nb_streams; ist1++) {
2035  AVStream *st1 = s->streams[ist1];
2036  for (ist2 = 0; ist2 < s->nb_streams; ist2++) {
2037  AVStream *st2 = s->streams[ist2];
2038  int i1, i2;
2039 
2040  if (ist1 == ist2)
2041  continue;
2042 
2043  for (i1 = i2 = 0; i1 < st1->nb_index_entries; i1++) {
2044  AVIndexEntry *e1 = &st1->index_entries[i1];
2045  int64_t e1_pts = av_rescale_q(e1->timestamp, st1->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
2046 
2047  skip = FFMAX(skip, e1->size);
2048  for (; i2 < st2->nb_index_entries; i2++) {
2049  AVIndexEntry *e2 = &st2->index_entries[i2];
2050  int64_t e2_pts = av_rescale_q(e2->timestamp, st2->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
2051  if (e2_pts - e1_pts < time_tolerance)
2052  continue;
2053  pos_delta = FFMAX(pos_delta, e1->pos - e2->pos);
2054  break;
2055  }
2056  }
2057  }
2058  }
2059 
2060  pos_delta *= 2;
2061  /* XXX This could be adjusted depending on protocol*/
2062  if (s->pb->buffer_size < pos_delta && pos_delta < (1<<24)) {
2063  av_log(s, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Reconfiguring buffers to size %"PRId64"\n", pos_delta);
2064  ffio_set_buf_size(s->pb, pos_delta);
2065  s->pb->short_seek_threshold = FFMAX(s->pb->short_seek_threshold, pos_delta/2);
2066  }
2067 
2068  if (skip < (1<<23)) {
2069  s->pb->short_seek_threshold = FFMAX(s->pb->short_seek_threshold, skip);
2070  }
2071 }
2072 
2073 int av_index_search_timestamp(AVStream *st, int64_t wanted_timestamp, int flags)
2074 {
2075  return ff_index_search_timestamp(st->index_entries, st->nb_index_entries,
2076  wanted_timestamp, flags);
2077 }

2079 static int64_t ff_read_timestamp(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index, int64_t *ppos, int64_t pos_limit,
2080  int64_t (*read_timestamp)(struct AVFormatContext *, int , int64_t *, int64_t ))
2081 {
2082  int64_t ts = read_timestamp(s, stream_index, ppos, pos_limit);
2083  if (stream_index >= 0)
2084  ts = wrap_timestamp(s->streams[stream_index], ts);
2085  return ts;
2086 }
