2088 int ff_seek_frame_binary(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index,
2089  int64_t target_ts, int flags)
2090 {
2091  AVInputFormat *avif = s->iformat;
2092  int64_t av_uninit(pos_min), av_uninit(pos_max), pos, pos_limit;
2093  int64_t ts_min, ts_max, ts;
2094  int index;
2095  int64_t ret;
2096  AVStream *st;
2097 
2098  if (stream_index < 0)
2099  return -1;
2100 
2101  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE, "read_seek: %d %s\n", stream_index, av_ts2str(target_ts));
2102 
2103  ts_max =
2104  ts_min = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
2105  pos_limit = -1; // GCC falsely says it may be uninitialized.
2106 
2107  st = s->streams[stream_index];
2108  if (st->index_entries) {
2109  AVIndexEntry *e;
2110 
2111  /* FIXME: Whole function must be checked for non-keyframe entries in
2112  * index case, especially read_timestamp(). */
2113  index = av_index_search_timestamp(st, target_ts,
2114  flags | AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD);
2115  index = FFMAX(index, 0);
2116  e = &st->index_entries[index];
2117 
2118  if (e->timestamp <= target_ts || e->pos == e->min_distance) {
2119  pos_min = e->pos;
2120  ts_min = e->timestamp;
2121  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE, "using cached pos_min=0x%"PRIx64" dts_min=%s\n",
2122  pos_min, av_ts2str(ts_min));
2123  } else {
2124  av_assert1(index == 0);
2125  }
2126 
2127  index = av_index_search_timestamp(st, target_ts,
2128  flags & ~AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD);
2129  av_assert0(index < st->nb_index_entries);
2130  if (index >= 0) {
2131  e = &st->index_entries[index];
2132  av_assert1(e->timestamp >= target_ts);
2133  pos_max = e->pos;
2134  ts_max = e->timestamp;
2135  pos_limit = pos_max - e->min_distance;
2136  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE, "using cached pos_max=0x%"PRIx64" pos_limit=0x%"PRIx64
2137  " dts_max=%s\n", pos_max, pos_limit, av_ts2str(ts_max));
2138  }
2139  }
2140 
2141  pos = ff_gen_search(s, stream_index, target_ts, pos_min, pos_max, pos_limit,
2142  ts_min, ts_max, flags, &ts, avif->read_timestamp);
2143  if (pos < 0)
2144  return -1;
2145 
2146  /* do the seek */
2147  if ((ret = avio_seek(s->pb, pos, SEEK_SET)) < 0)
2148  return ret;
2149 
2150  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2151  ff_update_cur_dts(s, st, ts);
2152 
2153  return 0;
2154 }
2155 
2156 int ff_find_last_ts(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index, int64_t *ts, int64_t *pos,
2157  int64_t (*read_timestamp)(struct AVFormatContext *, int , int64_t *, int64_t ))
2158 {
2159  int64_t step = 1024;
2160  int64_t limit, ts_max;
2161  int64_t filesize = avio_size(s->pb);
2162  int64_t pos_max = filesize - 1;
2163  do {
2164  limit = pos_max;
2165  pos_max = FFMAX(0, (pos_max) - step);
2166  ts_max = ff_read_timestamp(s, stream_index,
2167  &pos_max, limit, read_timestamp);
2168  step += step;
2169  } while (ts_max == AV_NOPTS_VALUE && 2*limit > step);
2170  if (ts_max == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2171  return -1;
2172 
2173  for (;;) {
2174  int64_t tmp_pos = pos_max + 1;
2175  int64_t tmp_ts = ff_read_timestamp(s, stream_index,
2176  &tmp_pos, INT64_MAX, read_timestamp);
2177  if (tmp_ts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2178  break;
2179  av_assert0(tmp_pos > pos_max);
2180  ts_max = tmp_ts;
2181  pos_max = tmp_pos;
2182  if (tmp_pos >= filesize)
2183  break;
2184  }
2185 
2186  if (ts)
2187  *ts = ts_max;
2188  if (pos)
2189  *pos = pos_max;
2190 
2191  return 0;
2192 }
2193 
2194 int64_t ff_gen_search(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index, int64_t target_ts,
2195  int64_t pos_min, int64_t pos_max, int64_t pos_limit,
2196  int64_t ts_min, int64_t ts_max,
2197  int flags, int64_t *ts_ret,
2198  int64_t (*read_timestamp)(struct AVFormatContext *, int,
2199  int64_t *, int64_t))
2200 {
2201  int64_t pos, ts;
2202  int64_t start_pos;
2203  int no_change;
2204  int ret;
2205 
2206  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE, "gen_seek: %d %s\n", stream_index, av_ts2str(target_ts));
2207 
2208  if (ts_min == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2209  pos_min = s->internal->data_offset;
2210  ts_min = ff_read_timestamp(s, stream_index, &pos_min, INT64_MAX, read_timestamp);
2211  if (ts_min == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2212  return -1;
2213  }
2214 
2215  if (ts_min >= target_ts) {
2216  *ts_ret = ts_min;
2217  return pos_min;
2218  }
2219 
2220  if (ts_max == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2221  if ((ret = ff_find_last_ts(s, stream_index, &ts_max, &pos_max, read_timestamp)) < 0)
2222  return ret;
2223  pos_limit = pos_max;
2224  }
2225 
2226  if (ts_max <= target_ts) {
2227  *ts_ret = ts_max;
2228  return pos_max;
2229  }
2230 
2231  av_assert0(ts_min < ts_max);
2232 
2233  no_change = 0;
2234  while (pos_min < pos_limit) {
2235  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE,
2236  "pos_min=0x%"PRIx64" pos_max=0x%"PRIx64" dts_min=%s dts_max=%s\n",
2237  pos_min, pos_max, av_ts2str(ts_min), av_ts2str(ts_max));
2238  av_assert0(pos_limit <= pos_max);
2239 
2240  if (no_change == 0) {
2241  int64_t approximate_keyframe_distance = pos_max - pos_limit;
2242  // interpolate position (better than dichotomy)
2243  pos = av_rescale(target_ts - ts_min, pos_max - pos_min,
2244  ts_max - ts_min) +
2245  pos_min - approximate_keyframe_distance;
2246  } else if (no_change == 1) {
2247  // bisection if interpolation did not change min / max pos last time
2248  pos = (pos_min + pos_limit) >> 1;
2249  } else {
2250  /* linear search if bisection failed, can only happen if there
2251  * are very few or no keyframes between min/max */
2252  pos = pos_min;
2253  }
2254  if (pos <= pos_min)
2255  pos = pos_min + 1;
2256  else if (pos > pos_limit)
2257  pos = pos_limit;
2258  start_pos = pos;
2259 
2260  // May pass pos_limit instead of -1.
2261  ts = ff_read_timestamp(s, stream_index, &pos, INT64_MAX, read_timestamp);
2262  if (pos == pos_max)
2263  no_change++;
2264  else
2265  no_change = 0;
2266  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE, "%"PRId64" %"PRId64" %"PRId64" / %s %s %s"
2267  " target:%s limit:%"PRId64" start:%"PRId64" noc:%d\n",
2268  pos_min, pos, pos_max,
2269  av_ts2str(ts_min), av_ts2str(ts), av_ts2str(ts_max), av_ts2str(target_ts),
2270  pos_limit, start_pos, no_change);
2271  if (ts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2272  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "read_timestamp() failed in the middle\n");
2273  return -1;
2274  }
2275  if (target_ts <= ts) {
2276  pos_limit = start_pos - 1;
2277  pos_max = pos;
2278  ts_max = ts;
2279  }
2280  if (target_ts >= ts) {
2281  pos_min = pos;
2282  ts_min = ts;
2283  }
2284  }
2285 
2286  pos = (flags & AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD) ? pos_min : pos_max;
2287  ts = (flags & AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD) ? ts_min : ts_max;
2288 #if 0
2289  pos_min = pos;
2290  ts_min = ff_read_timestamp(s, stream_index, &pos_min, INT64_MAX, read_timestamp);
2291  pos_min++;
2292  ts_max = ff_read_timestamp(s, stream_index, &pos_min, INT64_MAX, read_timestamp);
2293  av_log(s, AV_LOG_TRACE, "pos=0x%"PRIx64" %s<=%s<=%s\n",
2294  pos, av_ts2str(ts_min), av_ts2str(target_ts), av_ts2str(ts_max));
2295 #endif
2296  *ts_ret = ts;
2297  return pos;
2298 }
2299 
2300 static int seek_frame_byte(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index,
2301  int64_t pos, int flags)
2302 {
2303  int64_t pos_min, pos_max;
2304 
2305  pos_min = s->internal->data_offset;
2306  pos_max = avio_size(s->pb) - 1;
2307 
2308  if (pos < pos_min)
2309  pos = pos_min;
2310  else if (pos > pos_max)
2311  pos = pos_max;
2312 
2313  avio_seek(s->pb, pos, SEEK_SET);
2314 
2315  s->io_repositioned = 1;
2316 
2317  return 0;
2318 }
2319 
2320 static int seek_frame_generic(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index,
2321  int64_t timestamp, int flags)
2322 {
2323  int index;
2324  int64_t ret;
2325  AVStream *st;
2326  AVIndexEntry *ie;
2327 
2328  st = s->streams[stream_index];
2329 
2330  index = av_index_search_timestamp(st, timestamp, flags);
2331 
2332  if (index < 0 && st->nb_index_entries &&
2333  timestamp < st->index_entries[0].timestamp)
2334  return -1;
2335 
2336  if (index < 0 || index == st->nb_index_entries - 1) {
2337  AVPacket pkt;
2338  int nonkey = 0;
2339 
2340  if (st->nb_index_entries) {
2341  av_assert0(st->index_entries);
2342  ie = &st->index_entries[st->nb_index_entries - 1];
2343  if ((ret = avio_seek(s->pb, ie->pos, SEEK_SET)) < 0)
2344  return ret;
2345  ff_update_cur_dts(s, st, ie->timestamp);
2346  } else {
2347  if ((ret = avio_seek(s->pb, s->internal->data_offset, SEEK_SET)) < 0)
2348  return ret;
2349  }
2350  for (;;) {
2351  int read_status;
2352  do {
2353  read_status = av_read_frame(s, &pkt);
2354  } while (read_status == AVERROR(EAGAIN));
2355  if (read_status < 0)
2356  break;
2357  if (stream_index == pkt.stream_index && pkt.dts > timestamp) {
2358  if (pkt.flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY) {
2359  av_packet_unref(&pkt);
2360  break;
2361  }
2362  if (nonkey++ > 1000 && st->codecpar->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_CDGRAPHICS) {
2363  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR,"seek_frame_generic failed as this stream seems to contain no keyframes after the target timestamp, %d non keyframes found\n", nonkey);
2364  av_packet_unref(&pkt);
2365  break;
2366  }
2367  }
2368  av_packet_unref(&pkt);
2369  }
2370  index = av_index_search_timestamp(st, timestamp, flags);
2371  }
2372  if (index < 0)
2373  return -1;
2374 
2375  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2376  if (s->iformat->read_seek)
2377  if (s->iformat->read_seek(s, stream_index, timestamp, flags) >= 0)
2378  return 0;
2379  ie = &st->index_entries[index];
2380  if ((ret = avio_seek(s->pb, ie->pos, SEEK_SET)) < 0)
2381  return ret;
2382  ff_update_cur_dts(s, st, ie->timestamp);
2383 
2384  return 0;
2385 }
2386 
2387 static int seek_frame_internal(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index,
2388  int64_t timestamp, int flags)
2389 {
2390  int ret;
2391  AVStream *st;
2392 
2393  if (flags & AVSEEK_FLAG_BYTE) {
2394  if (s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NO_BYTE_SEEK)
2395  return -1;
2396  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2397  return seek_frame_byte(s, stream_index, timestamp, flags);
2398  }
2399 
2400  if (stream_index < 0) {
2401  stream_index = av_find_default_stream_index(s);
2402  if (stream_index < 0)
2403  return -1;
2404 
2405  st = s->streams[stream_index];
2406  /* timestamp for default must be expressed in AV_TIME_BASE units */
2407  timestamp = av_rescale(timestamp, st->time_base.den,
2408  AV_TIME_BASE * (int64_t) st->time_base.num);
2409  }
2410 
2411  /* first, we try the format specific seek */
2412  if (s->iformat->read_seek) {
2413  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2414  ret = s->iformat->read_seek(s, stream_index, timestamp, flags);
2415  } else
2416  ret = -1;
2417  if (ret >= 0)
2418  return 0;
2419 
2420  if (s->iformat->read_timestamp &&
2421  !(s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOBINSEARCH)) {
2422  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2423  return ff_seek_frame_binary(s, stream_index, timestamp, flags);
2424  } else if (!(s->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOGENSEARCH)) {
2425  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2426  return seek_frame_generic(s, stream_index, timestamp, flags);
2427  } else
2428  return -1;
2429 }
2430 
2431 int av_seek_frame(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index,
2432  int64_t timestamp, int flags)
2433 {
2434  int ret;
2435 
2436  if (s->iformat->read_seek2 && !s->iformat->read_seek) {
2437  int64_t min_ts = INT64_MIN, max_ts = INT64_MAX;
2438  if ((flags & AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD))
2439  max_ts = timestamp;
2440  else
2441  min_ts = timestamp;
2442  return avformat_seek_file(s, stream_index, min_ts, timestamp, max_ts,
2443  flags & ~AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD);
2444  }
2445 
2446  ret = seek_frame_internal(s, stream_index, timestamp, flags);
2447 
2448  if (ret >= 0)
2449  ret = avformat_queue_attached_pictures(s);
2450 
2451  return ret;
2452 }
2453 
2454 int avformat_seek_file(AVFormatContext *s, int stream_index, int64_t min_ts,
2455  int64_t ts, int64_t max_ts, int flags)
2456 {
2457  if (min_ts > ts || max_ts < ts)
2458  return -1;
2459  if (stream_index < -1 || stream_index >= (int)s->nb_streams)
2460  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
2461 
2462  if (s->seek2any>0)
2463  flags |= AVSEEK_FLAG_ANY;
2464  flags &= ~AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD;
2465 
2466  if (s->iformat->read_seek2) {
2467  int ret;
2468  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2469 
2470  if (stream_index == -1 && s->nb_streams == 1) {
2471  AVRational time_base = s->streams[0]->time_base;
2472  ts = av_rescale_q(ts, AV_TIME_BASE_Q, time_base);
2473  min_ts = av_rescale_rnd(min_ts, time_base.den,
2474  time_base.num * (int64_t)AV_TIME_BASE,
2475  AV_ROUND_UP | AV_ROUND_PASS_MINMAX);
2476  max_ts = av_rescale_rnd(max_ts, time_base.den,
2477  time_base.num * (int64_t)AV_TIME_BASE,
2478  AV_ROUND_DOWN | AV_ROUND_PASS_MINMAX);
2479  stream_index = 0;
2480  }
2481 
2482  ret = s->iformat->read_seek2(s, stream_index, min_ts,
2483  ts, max_ts, flags);
2484 
2485  if (ret >= 0)
2486  ret = avformat_queue_attached_pictures(s);
2487  return ret;
2488  }
2489 
2490  if (s->iformat->read_timestamp) {
2491  // try to seek via read_timestamp()
2492  }
2493 
2494  // Fall back on old API if new is not implemented but old is.
2495  // Note the old API has somewhat different semantics.
2496  if (s->iformat->read_seek || 1) {
2497  int dir = (ts - (uint64_t)min_ts > (uint64_t)max_ts - ts ? AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD : 0);
2498  int ret = av_seek_frame(s, stream_index, ts, flags | dir);
2499  if (ret<0 && ts != min_ts && max_ts != ts) {
2500  ret = av_seek_frame(s, stream_index, dir ? max_ts : min_ts, flags | dir);
2501  if (ret >= 0)
2502  ret = av_seek_frame(s, stream_index, ts, flags | (dir^AVSEEK_FLAG_BACKWARD));
2503  }
2504  return ret;
2505  }
2506 
2507  // try some generic seek like seek_frame_generic() but with new ts semantics
2508  return -1; //unreachable
2509 }
2510 
2511 int avformat_flush(AVFormatContext *s)
2512 {
2513  ff_read_frame_flush(s);
2514  return 0;
2515 }
2516 
2517 /*******************************************************/
2518 
2519 /**
2520  * Return TRUE if the stream has accurate duration in any stream.
2521  *
2522  * @return TRUE if the stream has accurate duration for at least one component.
2523  */
2524 static int has_duration(AVFormatContext *ic)
2525 {
2526  int i;
2527  AVStream *st;
2528 
2529  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2530  st = ic->streams[i];
2531  if (st->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2532  return 1;
2533  }
2534  if (ic->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2535  return 1;
2536  return 0;
2537 }
2538 
2539 /**
2540  * Estimate the stream timings from the one of each components.
2541  *
2542  * Also computes the global bitrate if possible.
2543  */
2544 static void update_stream_timings(AVFormatContext *ic)
2545 {
2546  int64_t start_time, start_time1, start_time_text, end_time, end_time1, end_time_text;
2547  int64_t duration, duration1, filesize;
2548  int i;
2549  AVStream *st;
2550  AVProgram *p;
2551 
2552  start_time = INT64_MAX;
2553  start_time_text = INT64_MAX;
2554  end_time = INT64_MIN;
2555  end_time_text = INT64_MIN;
2556  duration = INT64_MIN;
2557  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2558  st = ic->streams[i];
2559  if (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && st->time_base.den) {
2560  start_time1 = av_rescale_q(st->start_time, st->time_base,
2561  AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
2562  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE || st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA) {
2563  if (start_time1 < start_time_text)
2564  start_time_text = start_time1;
2565  } else
2566  start_time = FFMIN(start_time, start_time1);
2567  end_time1 = av_rescale_q_rnd(st->duration, st->time_base,
2568  AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
2569  AV_ROUND_NEAR_INF|AV_ROUND_PASS_MINMAX);
2570  if (end_time1 != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && (end_time1 > 0 ? start_time1 <= INT64_MAX - end_time1 : start_time1 >= INT64_MIN - end_time1)) {
2571  end_time1 += start_time1;
2572  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE || st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA)
2573  end_time_text = FFMAX(end_time_text, end_time1);
2574  else
2575  end_time = FFMAX(end_time, end_time1);
2576  }
2577  for (p = NULL; (p = av_find_program_from_stream(ic, p, i)); ) {
2578  if (p->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE || p->start_time > start_time1)
2579  p->start_time = start_time1;
2580  if (p->end_time < end_time1)
2581  p->end_time = end_time1;
2582  }
2583  }
2584  if (st->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2585  duration1 = av_rescale_q(st->duration, st->time_base,
2586  AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
2587  duration = FFMAX(duration, duration1);
2588  }
2589  }
2590  if (start_time == INT64_MAX || (start_time > start_time_text && start_time - start_time_text < AV_TIME_BASE))
2591  start_time = start_time_text;
2592  else if (start_time > start_time_text)
2593  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Ignoring outlier non primary stream starttime %f\n", start_time_text / (float)AV_TIME_BASE);
2594 
2595  if (end_time == INT64_MIN || (end_time < end_time_text && end_time_text - end_time < AV_TIME_BASE)) {
2596  end_time = end_time_text;
2597  } else if (end_time < end_time_text) {
2598  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Ignoring outlier non primary stream endtime %f\n", end_time_text / (float)AV_TIME_BASE);
2599  }
2600 
2601  if (start_time != INT64_MAX) {
2602  ic->start_time = start_time;
2603  if (end_time != INT64_MIN) {
2604  if (ic->nb_programs > 1) {
2605  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_programs; i++) {
2606  p = ic->programs[i];
2607  if (p->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2608  p->end_time > p->start_time &&
2609  p->end_time - (uint64_t)p->start_time <= INT64_MAX)
2610  duration = FFMAX(duration, p->end_time - p->start_time);
2611  }
2612  } else if (end_time >= start_time && end_time - (uint64_t)start_time <= INT64_MAX) {
2613  duration = FFMAX(duration, end_time - start_time);
2614  }
2615  }
2616  }
2617  if (duration != INT64_MIN && duration > 0 && ic->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2618  ic->duration = duration;
2619  }
2620  if (ic->pb && (filesize = avio_size(ic->pb)) > 0 && ic->duration > 0) {
2621  /* compute the bitrate */
2622  double bitrate = (double) filesize * 8.0 * AV_TIME_BASE /
2623  (double) ic->duration;
2624  if (bitrate >= 0 && bitrate <= INT64_MAX)
2625  ic->bit_rate = bitrate;
2626  }
2627 }
2628 
2629 static void fill_all_stream_timings(AVFormatContext *ic)
2630 {
2631  int i;
2632  AVStream *st;
2633 
2634  update_stream_timings(ic);
2635  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2636  st = ic->streams[i];
2637  if (st->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2638  if (ic->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2639  st->start_time = av_rescale_q(ic->start_time, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
2640  st->time_base);
2641  if (ic->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2642  st->duration = av_rescale_q(ic->duration, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
2643  st->time_base);
2644  }
2645  }
2646 }
2647 //+: estimate duration according to bitrate and filesize
2648 static void estimate_timings_from_bit_rate(AVFormatContext *ic)
2649 {
2650  int64_t filesize, duration;
2651  int i, show_warning = 0;
2652  AVStream *st;
2653 
2654  /* if bit_rate is already set, we believe it */
2655  if (ic->bit_rate <= 0) {
2656  int64_t bit_rate = 0;
2657  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2658  st = ic->streams[i];
2659  if (st->codecpar->bit_rate <= 0 && st->internal->avctx->bit_rate > 0)
2660  st->codecpar->bit_rate = st->internal->avctx->bit_rate;
2661  if (st->codecpar->bit_rate > 0) {
2662  if (INT64_MAX - st->codecpar->bit_rate < bit_rate) {
2663  bit_rate = 0;
2664  break;
2665  }
2666  bit_rate += st->codecpar->bit_rate;//+: accumulate bitrate of all streams
2667  } else if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO && st->codec_info_nb_frames > 1) {
2668  // If we have a videostream with packets but without a bitrate
2669  // then consider the sum not known
2670  bit_rate = 0;
2671  break;
2672  }
2673  }
2674  ic->bit_rate = bit_rate;
2675  }
2676 
2677  /* if duration is already set, we believe it */
2678  if (ic->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2679  ic->bit_rate != 0) {
2680  filesize = ic->pb ? avio_size(ic->pb) : 0;
2681  if (filesize > ic->internal->data_offset) {
2682  filesize -= ic->internal->data_offset;
2683  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2684  st = ic->streams[i];
2685  if ( st->time_base.num <= INT64_MAX / ic->bit_rate
2686  && st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2687  //+: duration_in_sec=8*filesize/bitrate
2688  //+: duration=duration_in_sec/time_base
2689  duration = av_rescale(8 * filesize, st->time_base.den,
2690  ic->bit_rate *
2691  (int64_t) st->time_base.num);
2692  st->duration = duration;
2693  show_warning = 1;
2694  }
2695  }
2696  }
2697  }
2698  if (show_warning)
2699  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
2700  "Estimating duration from bitrate, this may be inaccurate\n");
2701 }
2702 
2703 #define DURATION_MAX_READ_SIZE 250000LL
2704 #define DURATION_MAX_RETRY 6
2705 
2706 /* only usable for MPEG-PS streams */
2707 static void estimate_timings_from_pts(AVFormatContext *ic, int64_t old_offset)
2708 {
2709  AVPacket pkt1, *pkt = &pkt1;
2710  AVStream *st;
2711  int num, den, read_size, i, ret;
2712  int found_duration = 0;
2713  int is_end;
2714  int64_t filesize, offset, duration;
2715  int retry = 0;
2716 
2717  /* flush packet queue */
2718  flush_packet_queue(ic);
2719 
2720  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2721  st = ic->streams[i];
2722  if (st->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2723  st->first_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2724  st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN)
2725  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
2726  "start time for stream %d is not set in estimate_timings_from_pts\n", i);
2727 
2728  if (st->parser) {
2729  av_parser_close(st->parser);
2730  st->parser = NULL;
2731  }
2732  }
2733 
2734  av_opt_set(ic, "skip_changes", "1", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
2735  /* estimate the end time (duration) */
2736  /* XXX: may need to support wrapping */
2737  filesize = ic->pb ? avio_size(ic->pb) : 0;
2738  do {
2739  is_end = found_duration;
2740  //+: Try the nearest position of end first
2741  //+: Because from the end pts get the most accurate duration
2742  //+: the more retry times, the offset will be small
2743  offset = filesize - (DURATION_MAX_READ_SIZE << retry);
2744  if (offset < 0)
2745  offset = 0;
2746 
2747  avio_seek(ic->pb, offset, SEEK_SET);
2748  read_size = 0;
2749  for (;;) {
2750  //exit until the read_size exceeds MAX READ SIZE
2751  if (read_size >= DURATION_MAX_READ_SIZE << (FFMAX(retry - 1, 0)))
2752  break;
2753 
2754  do {
2755  ret = ff_read_packet(ic, pkt);//+: get the last valid packet
2756  } while (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN));
2757  if (ret != 0)
2758  break;
2759  read_size += pkt->size;
2760  st = ic->streams[pkt->stream_index];
2761  if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2762  (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
2763  st->first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)) {
2764  //+: get duration of current packet
2765  //+: add pkt duration, we can get much more accurate duration
2766  if (pkt->duration == 0) {
2767  ff_compute_frame_duration(ic, &num, &den, st, st->parser, pkt);
2768  if (den && num) {
2769  //+: get duration of time_base
2770  pkt->duration = av_rescale_rnd(1,
2771  num * (int64_t) st->time_base.den,
2772  den * (int64_t) st->time_base.num,
2773  AV_ROUND_DOWN);
2774  }
2775  }
2776  //+:pts of last packet plus its duration to get the duration of total file
2777  duration = pkt->pts + pkt->duration;
2778  found_duration = 1;
2779  //+: if start_time is not 0, minus it
2780  if (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2781  duration -= st->start_time;
2782  else
2783  duration -= st->first_dts;
2784  if (duration > 0) {
2785  if (st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE || st->info->last_duration<= 0 ||
2786  (st->duration < duration && FFABS(duration - st->info->last_duration) < 60LL*st->time_base.den / st->time_base.num))
2787  st->duration = duration;
2788  st->info->last_duration = duration;
2789  }
2790  }
2791  av_packet_unref(pkt);
2792  }
2793 
2794  /* check if all audio/video streams have valid duration */
2795  if (!is_end) {
2796  is_end = 1;
2797  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2798  st = ic->streams[i];
2799  switch (st->codecpar->codec_type) {
2800  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2801  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2802  if (st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2803  is_end = 0;
2804  }
2805  }
2806  }
2807  } while (!is_end &&
2808  offset &&
2809  ++retry <= DURATION_MAX_RETRY);
2810 
2811  av_opt_set(ic, "skip_changes", "0", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
2812 
2813  /* warn about audio/video streams which duration could not be estimated */
2814  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2815  st = ic->streams[i];
2816  if (st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2817  switch (st->codecpar->codec_type) {
2818  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2819  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2820  if (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE || st->first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2821  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "stream %d : no PTS found at end of file, duration not set\n", i);
2822  } else
2823  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "stream %d : no TS found at start of file, duration not set\n", i);
2824  }
2825  }
2826  }
2827  fill_all_stream_timings(ic);
2828 
2829  avio_seek(ic->pb, old_offset, SEEK_SET);
2830  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2831  int j;
2832 
2833  st = ic->streams[i];
2834  st->cur_dts = st->first_dts;
2835  st->last_IP_pts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
2836  st->last_dts_for_order_check = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
2837  for (j = 0; j < MAX_REORDER_DELAY + 1; j++)
2838  st->pts_buffer[j] = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
2839  }
2840 }
2841 
2842 static void estimate_timings(AVFormatContext *ic, int64_t old_offset)
2843 {
2844  int64_t file_size;
2845 
2846  /* get the file size, if possible */
2847  if (ic->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOFILE) {
2848  file_size = 0;
2849  } else {
2850  file_size = avio_size(ic->pb);
2851  file_size = FFMAX(0, file_size);
2852  }
2853 
2854  if ((!strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpeg") ||
2855  !strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpegts")) &&
2856  file_size && ic->pb->seekable) {
2857  /* get accurate estimate from the PTSes */
2858  estimate_timings_from_pts(ic, old_offset);
2859  ic->duration_estimation_method = AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_PTS;
2860  } else if (has_duration(ic)) {
2861  /* at least one component has timings - we use them for all
2862  * the components */
2863  fill_all_stream_timings(ic);
2864  ic->duration_estimation_method = AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_STREAM;
2865  } else {
2866  /* less precise: use bitrate info */
2867  estimate_timings_from_bit_rate(ic);
2868  ic->duration_estimation_method = AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_BITRATE;
2869  }
2870  update_stream_timings(ic);
2871 
2872  {
2873  int i;
2874  AVStream av_unused *st;
2875  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2876  st = ic->streams[i];
2877  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_TRACE, "stream %d: start_time: %0.3f duration: %0.3f\n", i,
2878  (double) st->start_time * av_q2d(st->time_base),
2879  (double) st->duration * av_q2d(st->time_base));
2880  }
2881  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_TRACE,
2882  "format: start_time: %0.3f duration: %0.3f bitrate=%"PRId64" kb/s\n",
2883  (double) ic->start_time / AV_TIME_BASE,
2884  (double) ic->duration / AV_TIME_BASE,
2885  (int64_t)ic->bit_rate / 1000);
2886  }
2887 }
2888 
2889 static int has_codec_parameters(AVStream *st, const char **errmsg_ptr)
2890 {
2891  AVCodecContext *avctx = st->internal->avctx;
2892 
2893 #define FAIL(errmsg) do { \
2894  if (errmsg_ptr) \
2895  *errmsg_ptr = errmsg; \
2896  return 0; \
2897  } while (0)
2898 
2899  if ( avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_NONE
2900  && avctx->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA)
2901  FAIL("unknown codec");
2902  switch (avctx->codec_type) {
2903  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2904  if (!avctx->frame_size && determinable_frame_size(avctx))
2905  FAIL("unspecified frame size");
2906  if (st->info->found_decoder >= 0 &&
2907  avctx->sample_fmt == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE)
2908  FAIL("unspecified sample format");
2909  if (!avctx->sample_rate)
2910  FAIL("unspecified sample rate");
2911  if (!avctx->channels)
2912  FAIL("unspecified number of channels");
2913  if (st->info->found_decoder >= 0 && !st->nb_decoded_frames && avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_DTS)
2914  FAIL("no decodable DTS frames");
2915  break;
2916  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2917  if (!avctx->width)
2918  FAIL("unspecified size");
2919  if (st->info->found_decoder >= 0 && avctx->pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE)
2920  FAIL("unspecified pixel format");
2921  if (st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RV30 || st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RV40)
2922  if (!st->sample_aspect_ratio.num && !st->codecpar->sample_aspect_ratio.num && !st->codec_info_nb_frames)
2923  FAIL("no frame in rv30/40 and no sar");
2924  break;
2925  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE:
2926  if (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_HDMV_PGS_SUBTITLE && !avctx->width)
2927  FAIL("unspecified size");
2928  break;
2929  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
2930  if (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_NONE) return 1;
2931  }
2932 
2933  return 1;
2934 }

2936 /* returns 1 or 0 if or if not decoded data was returned, or a negative error */
2937 static int try_decode_frame(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st, AVPacket *avpkt,
2938  AVDictionary **options)
2939 {
2940  AVCodecContext *avctx = st->internal->avctx;
2941  const AVCodec *codec;
2942  int got_picture = 1, ret = 0;
2943  AVFrame *frame = av_frame_alloc();
2944  AVSubtitle subtitle;
2945  AVPacket pkt = *avpkt;
2946  int do_skip_frame = 0;
2947  enum AVDiscard skip_frame;
2948 
2949  if (!frame)
2950  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
2951 
2952  if (!avcodec_is_open(avctx) &&
2953  st->info->found_decoder <= 0 &&
2954  (st->codecpar->codec_id != -st->info->found_decoder || !st->codecpar->codec_id)) {
2955  AVDictionary *thread_opt = NULL;
2956 
2957  codec = find_probe_decoder(s, st, st->codecpar->codec_id);
2958 
2959  if (!codec) {
2960  st->info->found_decoder = -st->codecpar->codec_id;
2961  ret = -1;
2962  goto fail;
2963  }
2964 
2965  /* Force thread count to 1 since the H.264 decoder will not extract
2966  * SPS and PPS to extradata during multi-threaded decoding. */
2967  av_dict_set(options ? options : &thread_opt, "threads", "1", 0);
2968  if (s->codec_whitelist)
2969  av_dict_set(options ? options : &thread_opt, "codec_whitelist", s->codec_whitelist, 0);
2970  ret = avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, options ? options : &thread_opt);
2971  if (!options)
2972  av_dict_free(&thread_opt);
2973  if (ret < 0) {
2974  st->info->found_decoder = -avctx->codec_id;
2975  goto fail;
2976  }
2977  st->info->found_decoder = 1;
2978  } else if (!st->info->found_decoder)
2979  st->info->found_decoder = 1;
2980 
2981  if (st->info->found_decoder < 0) {
2982  ret = -1;
2983  goto fail;
2984  }
2985 
2986  if (avpriv_codec_get_cap_skip_frame_fill_param(avctx->codec)) {
2987  do_skip_frame = 1;
2988  skip_frame = avctx->skip_frame;
2989  avctx->skip_frame = AVDISCARD_ALL;
2990  }
2991 
2992  while ((pkt.size > 0 || (!pkt.data && got_picture)) &&
2993  ret >= 0 &&
2994  (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL) || !has_decode_delay_been_guessed(st) ||
2995  (!st->codec_info_nb_frames &&
2996  (avctx->codec->capabilities & AV_CODEC_CAP_CHANNEL_CONF)))) {
2997  got_picture = 0;
2998  if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
2999  avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
3000  ret = avcodec_send_packet(avctx, &pkt);
3001  if (ret < 0 && ret != AVERROR(EAGAIN) && ret != AVERROR_EOF)
3002  break;
3003  if (ret >= 0)
3004  pkt.size = 0;
3005  ret = avcodec_receive_frame(avctx, frame);
3006  if (ret >= 0)
3007  got_picture = 1;
3008  if (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN) || ret == AVERROR_EOF)
3009  ret = 0;
3010  } else if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) {
3011  ret = avcodec_decode_subtitle2(avctx, &subtitle,
3012  &got_picture, &pkt);
3013  if (ret >= 0)
3014  pkt.size = 0;
3015  }
3016  if (ret >= 0) {
3017  if (got_picture)
3018  st->nb_decoded_frames++;
3019  ret = got_picture;
3020  }
3021  }
3022 
3023  if (!pkt.data && !got_picture)
3024  ret = -1;
3025 
3026 fail:
3027  if (do_skip_frame) {
3028  avctx->skip_frame = skip_frame;
3029  }
3030 
3031  av_frame_free(&frame);
3032  return ret;
3033 }

3045 enum AVCodecID ff_codec_get_id(const AVCodecTag *tags, unsigned int tag)
3046 {
3047  int i;
3048  for (i = 0; tags[i].id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE; i++)
3049  if (tag == tags[i].tag)
3050  return tags[i].id;
3051  for (i = 0; tags[i].id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE; i++)
3052  if (avpriv_toupper4(tag) == avpriv_toupper4(tags[i].tag))
3053  return tags[i].id;
3054  return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3055 }

3057 enum AVCodecID ff_get_pcm_codec_id(int bps, int flt, int be, int sflags)
3058 {
3059  if (bps <= 0 || bps > 64)
3060  return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3061 
3062  if (flt) {
3063  switch (bps) {
3064  case 32:
3065  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F32BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F32LE;
3066  case 64:
3067  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F64BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F64LE;
3068  default:
3069  return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3070  }
3071  } else {
3072  bps += 7;
3073  bps >>= 3;
3074  if (sflags & (1 << (bps - 1))) {
3075  switch (bps) {
3076  case 1:
3077  return AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S8;
3078  case 2:
3079  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S16BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S16LE;
3080  case 3:
3081  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S24BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S24LE;
3082  case 4:
3083  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S32BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S32LE;
3084  case 8:
3085  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S64BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S64LE;
3086  default:
3087  return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3088  }
3089  } else {
3090  switch (bps) {
3091  case 1:
3092  return AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U8;
3093  case 2:
3094  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U16BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U16LE;
3095  case 3:
3096  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U24BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U24LE;
3097  case 4:
3098  return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U32BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U32LE;
3099  default:
3100  return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3101  }
3102  }
3103  }
3104 }

3110  return 0;

3114 int av_codec_get_tag2(const AVCodecTag * const *tags, enum AVCodecID id,
3115  unsigned int *tag)
3116 {

3118  for (i = 0; tags && tags[i]; i++) {
3119  const AVCodecTag *codec_tags = tags[i];
3120  while (codec_tags->id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE) {
3121  if (codec_tags->id == id) {
3122  *tag = codec_tags->tag;
3123  return 1;
3124  }
3125  codec_tags++;
3126  }
3127  }
3128  return 0;

3142 static void compute_chapters_end(AVFormatContext *s)
3143 {
3144  unsigned int i, j;
3145  int64_t max_time = 0;
3146 
3147  if (s->duration > 0 && s->start_time < INT64_MAX - s->duration)
3148  max_time = s->duration +
3149  ((s->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) ? 0 : s->start_time);
3150 
3151  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_chapters; i++)
3152  if (s->chapters[i]->end == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
3153  AVChapter *ch = s->chapters[i];
3154  int64_t end = max_time ? av_rescale_q(max_time, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
3155  ch->time_base)
3156  : INT64_MAX;
3157 
3158  for (j = 0; j < s->nb_chapters; j++) {
3159  AVChapter *ch1 = s->chapters[j];
3160  int64_t next_start = av_rescale_q(ch1->start, ch1->time_base,
3161  ch->time_base);
3162  if (j != i && next_start > ch->start && next_start < end)
3163  end = next_start;
3164  }
3165  ch->end = (end == INT64_MAX) ? ch->start : end;
3166  }
3167 }
3168 
3169 static int get_std_framerate(int i)
3170 {
3171  if (i < 30*12)
3172  return (i + 1) * 1001;
3173  i -= 30*12;
3174 
3175  if (i < 30)
3176  return (i + 31) * 1001 * 12;
3177  i -= 30;
3178 
3179  if (i < 3)
3180  return ((const int[]) { 80, 120, 240})[i] * 1001 * 12;
3181 
3182  i -= 3;
3183 
3184  return ((const int[]) { 24, 30, 60, 12, 15, 48 })[i] * 1000 * 12;
3185 }
3186 
3187 /* Is the time base unreliable?
3188  * This is a heuristic to balance between quick acceptance of the values in
3189  * the headers vs. some extra checks.
3190  * Old DivX and Xvid often have nonsense timebases like 1fps or 2fps.
3191  * MPEG-2 commonly misuses field repeat flags to store different framerates.
3192  * And there are "variable" fps files this needs to detect as well. */
3193 static int tb_unreliable(AVCodecContext *c)
3194 {
3195  if (c->time_base.den >= 101LL * c->time_base.num ||
3196  c->time_base.den < 5LL * c->time_base.num ||
3197  // c->codec_tag == AV_RL32("DIVX") ||
3198  // c->codec_tag == AV_RL32("XVID") ||
3199  c->codec_tag == AV_RL32("mp4v") ||
3200  c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MPEG2VIDEO ||
3201  c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_GIF ||
3202  c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC ||
3203  c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264)
3204  return 1;
3205  return 0;
3206 }

3208 int ff_alloc_extradata(AVCodecParameters *par, int size)
3209 {
3210  int ret;
3211 
3212  if (size < 0 || size >= INT32_MAX - AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE) {
3213  par->extradata = NULL;
3214  par->extradata_size = 0;
3215  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
3216  }
3217  par->extradata = av_malloc(size + AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE);
3218  if (par->extradata) {
3219  memset(par->extradata + size, 0, AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE);
3220  par->extradata_size = size;
3221  ret = 0;
3222  } else {
3223  par->extradata_size = 0;
3224  ret = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3225  }
3226  return ret;
3227 }

3229 int ff_get_extradata(AVFormatContext *s, AVCodecParameters *par, AVIOContext *pb, int size)
3230 {
3231  int ret = ff_alloc_extradata(par, size);
3232  if (ret < 0)
3233  return ret;
3234  ret = avio_read(pb, par->extradata, size);
3235  if (ret != size) {
3236  av_freep(&par->extradata);
3237  par->extradata_size = 0;
3238  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Failed to read extradata of size %d\n", size);
3239  return ret < 0 ? ret : AVERROR_INVALIDDATA;
3240  }
3241 
3242  return ret;
3243 }

3245 int ff_rfps_add_frame(AVFormatContext *ic, AVStream *st, int64_t ts)
3246 {
3247  int i, j;
3248  int64_t last = st->info->last_dts;
3249 
3250  if ( ts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && last != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && ts > last
3251  && ts - (uint64_t)last < INT64_MAX) {
3252  double dts = (is_relative(ts) ? ts - RELATIVE_TS_BASE : ts) * av_q2d(st->time_base);
3253  int64_t duration = ts - last;
3254 
3255  if (!st->info->duration_error)
3256  st->info->duration_error = av_mallocz(sizeof(st->info->duration_error[0])*2);
3257  if (!st->info->duration_error)
3258  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3259 
3260 // if (st->codec->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
3261 // av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "%f\n", dts);
3262  for (i = 0; i<MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; i++) {
3263  if (st->info->duration_error[0][1][i] < 1e10) {
3264  int framerate = get_std_framerate(i);
3265  double sdts = dts*framerate/(1001*12);
3266  for (j= 0; j<2; j++) {
3267  int64_t ticks = llrint(sdts+j*0.5);
3268  double error= sdts - ticks + j*0.5;
3269  st->info->duration_error[j][0][i] += error;
3270  st->info->duration_error[j][1][i] += error*error;
3271  }
3272  }
3273  }
3274  st->info->duration_count++;
3275  st->info->rfps_duration_sum += duration;
3276 
3277  if (st->info->duration_count % 10 == 0) {
3278  int n = st->info->duration_count;
3279  for (i = 0; i<MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; i++) {
3280  if (st->info->duration_error[0][1][i] < 1e10) {
3281  double a0 = st->info->duration_error[0][0][i] / n;
3282  double error0 = st->info->duration_error[0][1][i] / n - a0*a0;
3283  double a1 = st->info->duration_error[1][0][i] / n;
3284  double error1 = st->info->duration_error[1][1][i] / n - a1*a1;
3285  if (error0 > 0.04 && error1 > 0.04) {
3286  st->info->duration_error[0][1][i] = 2e10;
3287  st->info->duration_error[1][1][i] = 2e10;
3288  }
3289  }
3290  }
3291  }
3292 
3293  // ignore the first 4 values, they might have some random jitter
3294  if (st->info->duration_count > 3 && is_relative(ts) == is_relative(last))
3295  st->info->duration_gcd = av_gcd(st->info->duration_gcd, duration);
3296  }
3297  if (ts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
3298  st->info->last_dts = ts;
3299 
3300  return 0;
3301 }
3302 
3303 void ff_rfps_calculate(AVFormatContext *ic)
3304 {
3305  int i, j;
3306 
3307  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3308  AVStream *st = ic->streams[i];
3309 
3310  if (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
3311  continue;
3312  // the check for tb_unreliable() is not completely correct, since this is not about handling
3313  // an unreliable/inexact time base, but a time base that is finer than necessary, as e.g.
3314  // ipmovie.c produces.
3315  if (tb_unreliable(st->internal->avctx) && st->info->duration_count > 15 && st->info->duration_gcd > FFMAX(1, st->time_base.den/(500LL*st->time_base.num)) && !st->r_frame_rate.num)
3316  av_reduce(&st->r_frame_rate.num, &st->r_frame_rate.den, st->time_base.den, st->time_base.num * st->info->duration_gcd, INT_MAX);
3317  if (st->info->duration_count>1 && !st->r_frame_rate.num
3318  && tb_unreliable(st->internal->avctx)) {
3319  int num = 0;
3320  double best_error= 0.01;
3321  AVRational ref_rate = st->r_frame_rate.num ? st->r_frame_rate : av_inv_q(st->time_base);
3322 
3323  for (j= 0; j<MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; j++) {
3324  int k;
3325 
3326  if (st->info->codec_info_duration &&
3327  st->info->codec_info_duration*av_q2d(st->time_base) < (1001*11.5)/get_std_framerate(j))
3328  continue;
3329  if (!st->info->codec_info_duration && get_std_framerate(j) < 1001*12)
3330  continue;
3331 
3332  if (av_q2d(st->time_base) * st->info->rfps_duration_sum / st->info->duration_count < (1001*12.0 * 0.8)/get_std_framerate(j))
3333  continue;
3334 
3335  for (k= 0; k<2; k++) {
3336  int n = st->info->duration_count;
3337  double a= st->info->duration_error[k][0][j] / n;
3338  double error= st->info->duration_error[k][1][j]/n - a*a;
3339 
3340  if (error < best_error && best_error> 0.000000001) {
3341  best_error= error;
3342  num = get_std_framerate(j);
3343  }
3344  if (error < 0.02)
3345  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "rfps: %f %f\n", get_std_framerate(j) / 12.0/1001, error);
3346  }
3347  }
3348  // do not increase frame rate by more than 1 % in order to match a standard rate.
3349  if (num && (!ref_rate.num || (double)num/(12*1001) < 1.01 * av_q2d(ref_rate)))
3350  av_reduce(&st->r_frame_rate.num, &st->r_frame_rate.den, num, 12*1001, INT_MAX);
3351  }
3352  if ( !st->avg_frame_rate.num
3353  && st->r_frame_rate.num && st->info->rfps_duration_sum
3354  && st->info->codec_info_duration <= 0
3355  && st->info->duration_count > 2
3356  && fabs(1.0 / (av_q2d(st->r_frame_rate) * av_q2d(st->time_base)) - st->info->rfps_duration_sum / (double)st->info->duration_count) <= 1.0
3357  ) {
3358  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "Setting avg frame rate based on r frame rate\n");
3359  st->avg_frame_rate = st->r_frame_rate;
3360  }
3361 
3362  av_freep(&st->info->duration_error);
3363  st->info->last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3364  st->info->duration_count = 0;
3365  st->info->rfps_duration_sum = 0;
3366  }
3367 }
3368 //+: Read packets of a media file to get stream information.
3369 //+: This is useful for file formats with no headers such as MPEG.
3370 //+: The logical file position is not changed by this function;
3371 //+: examined packets may be buffered for later processing.
3372 int avformat_find_stream_info(AVFormatContext *ic, AVDictionary **options)
3373 {
3374  int i, count = 0, ret = 0, j;
3375  int64_t read_size;
3376  AVStream *st;
3377  AVCodecContext *avctx;
3378  AVPacket pkt1, *pkt;
3379  int64_t old_offset = avio_tell(ic->pb);
3380  // new streams might appear, no options for those
3381  int orig_nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
3382  int flush_codecs;
3383  int64_t max_analyze_duration = ic->max_analyze_duration;
3384  int64_t max_stream_analyze_duration;
3385  int64_t max_subtitle_analyze_duration;
3386  int64_t probesize = ic->probesize;
3387  int eof_reached = 0;
3388  int *missing_streams = av_opt_ptr(ic->iformat->priv_class, ic->priv_data, "missing_streams");
3389 
3390  flush_codecs = probesize > 0;
3391 
3392  av_opt_set(ic, "skip_clear", "1", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
3393 
3394  max_stream_analyze_duration = max_analyze_duration;
3395  max_subtitle_analyze_duration = max_analyze_duration;
3396  if (!max_analyze_duration) {
3397  max_stream_analyze_duration =
3398  max_analyze_duration = 5*AV_TIME_BASE;
3399  max_subtitle_analyze_duration = 30*AV_TIME_BASE;
3400  if (!strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "flv"))
3401  max_stream_analyze_duration = 90*AV_TIME_BASE;
3402  if (!strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpeg") || !strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpegts"))
3403  max_stream_analyze_duration = 7*AV_TIME_BASE;
3404  }
3405 
3406  if (ic->pb)
3407  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "Before avformat_find_stream_info() pos: %"PRId64" bytes read:%"PRId64" seeks:%d nb_streams:%d\n",
3408  avio_tell(ic->pb), ic->pb->bytes_read, ic->pb->seek_count, ic->nb_streams);
3409 
3410  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3411  const AVCodec *codec;
3412  AVDictionary *thread_opt = NULL;
3413  st = ic->streams[i];
3414  avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3415 
3416  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
3417  st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) {
3418 /* if (!st->time_base.num)
3419  st->time_base = */
3420  if (!avctx->time_base.num)
3421  avctx->time_base = st->time_base;
3422  }
3423 
3424  /* check if the caller has overridden the codec id */
3425 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
3426 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
3427  if (st->codec->codec_id != st->internal->orig_codec_id) {
3428  st->codecpar->codec_id = st->codec->codec_id;
3429  st->codecpar->codec_type = st->codec->codec_type;
3430  st->internal->orig_codec_id = st->codec->codec_id;
3431  }
3432 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
3433 #endif
3434  // only for the split stuff
3435  if (!st->parser && !(ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOPARSE) && st->request_probe <= 0) {
3436  st->parser = av_parser_init(st->codecpar->codec_id);
3437  if (st->parser) {
3438  if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_HEADERS) {
3439  st->parser->flags |= PARSER_FLAG_COMPLETE_FRAMES;
3440  } else if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_FULL_RAW) {
3441  st->parser->flags |= PARSER_FLAG_USE_CODEC_TS;
3442  }
3443  } else if (st->need_parsing) {
3444  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "parser not found for codec "
3445  "%s, packets or times may be invalid.\n",
3446  avcodec_get_name(st->codecpar->codec_id));
3447  }
3448  }
3449 
3450  if (st->codecpar->codec_id != st->internal->orig_codec_id)
3451  st->internal->orig_codec_id = st->codecpar->codec_id;
3452 
3453  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(avctx, st->codecpar);
3454  if (ret < 0)
3455  goto find_stream_info_err;
3456  if (st->request_probe <= 0)
3457  st->internal->avctx_inited = 1;
3458 
3459  codec = find_probe_decoder(ic, st, st->codecpar->codec_id);
3460 
3461  /* Force thread count to 1 since the H.264 decoder will not extract
3462  * SPS and PPS to extradata during multi-threaded decoding. */
3463  av_dict_set(options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt, "threads", "1", 0);
3464 
3465  if (ic->codec_whitelist)
3466  av_dict_set(options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt, "codec_whitelist", ic->codec_whitelist, 0);
3467 
3468  /* Ensure that subtitle_header is properly set. */
3469  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE
3470  && codec && !avctx->codec) {
3471  if (avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt) < 0)
3472  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3473  "Failed to open codec in %s\n",__FUNCTION__);
3474  }
3475 
3476  // Try to just open decoders, in case this is enough to get parameters.
3477  if (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL) && st->request_probe <= 0) {
3478  if (codec && !avctx->codec)
3479  if (avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt) < 0)
3480  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3481  "Failed to open codec in %s\n",__FUNCTION__);
3482  }
3483  if (!options)
3484  av_dict_free(&thread_opt);
3485  }
3486 
3487  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3488 #if FF_API_R_FRAME_RATE
3489  ic->streams[i]->info->last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3490 #endif
3491  ic->streams[i]->info->fps_first_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3492  ic->streams[i]->info->fps_last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3493  }
3494 
3495  read_size = 0;
3496  for (;;) {
3497  int analyzed_all_streams;
3498  if (ff_check_interrupt(&ic->interrupt_callback)) {
3499  ret = AVERROR_EXIT;
3500  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "interrupted\n");
3501  break;
3502  }
3503 
3504  /* check if one codec still needs to be handled */
3505  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3506  int fps_analyze_framecount = 20;
3507 
3508  st = ic->streams[i];
3509  if (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL))
3510  break;
3511  /* If the timebase is coarse (like the usual millisecond precision
3512  * of mkv), we need to analyze more frames to reliably arrive at
3513  * the correct fps. */
3514  if (av_q2d(st->time_base) > 0.0005)
3515  fps_analyze_framecount *= 2;
3516  if (!tb_unreliable(st->internal->avctx))
3517  fps_analyze_framecount = 0;
3518  if (ic->fps_probe_size >= 0)
3519  fps_analyze_framecount = ic->fps_probe_size;
3520  if (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC)
3521  fps_analyze_framecount = 0;
3522  /* variable fps and no guess at the real fps */
3523  if (!(st->r_frame_rate.num && st->avg_frame_rate.num) &&
3524  st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3525  int count = (ic->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOTIMESTAMPS) ?
3526  st->info->codec_info_duration_fields/2 :
3527  st->info->duration_count;
3528  if (count < fps_analyze_framecount)
3529  break;
3530  }
3531  if (st->parser && st->parser->parser->split &&
3532  !st->internal->avctx->extradata)
3533  break;
3534  if (st->first_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
3535  !(ic->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOTIMESTAMPS) &&
3536  st->codec_info_nb_frames < ((st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC) ? 1 : ic->max_ts_probe) &&
3537  (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
3538  st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO))
3539  break;
3540  }
3541  analyzed_all_streams = 0;
3542  if (!missing_streams || !*missing_streams)
3543  if (i == ic->nb_streams) {
3544  analyzed_all_streams = 1;
3545  /* NOTE: If the format has no header, then we need to read some
3546  * packets to get most of the streams, so we cannot stop here. */
3547  if (!(ic->ctx_flags & AVFMTCTX_NOHEADER)) {
3548  /* If we found the info for all the codecs, we can stop. */
3549  ret = count;
3550  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "All info found\n");
3551  flush_codecs = 0;
3552  break;
3553  }
3554  }
3555  /* We did not get all the codec info, but we read too much data. */
3556  if (read_size >= probesize) {
3557  ret = count;
3558  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
3559  "Probe buffer size limit of %"PRId64" bytes reached\n", probesize);
3560  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++)
3561  if (!ic->streams[i]->r_frame_rate.num &&
3562  ic->streams[i]->info->duration_count <= 1 &&
3563  ic->streams[i]->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO &&
3564  strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "image2"))
3565  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3566  "Stream #%d: not enough frames to estimate rate; "
3567  "consider increasing probesize\n", i);
3568  break;
3569  }
3570 
3571  /* NOTE: A new stream can be added there if no header in file
3572  * (AVFMTCTX_NOHEADER). */
3573  ret = read_frame_internal(ic, &pkt1);
3574  if (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN))
3575  continue;
3576 
3577  if (ret < 0) {
3578  /* EOF or error*/
3579  eof_reached = 1;
3580  break;
3581  }
3582 
3583  pkt = &pkt1;
3584 
3585  if (!(ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOBUFFER)) {
3586  ret = add_to_pktbuf(&ic->internal->packet_buffer, pkt,
3587  &ic->internal->packet_buffer_end, 0);
3588  if (ret < 0)
3589  goto find_stream_info_err;
3590  }
3591 
3592  st = ic->streams[pkt->stream_index];
3593  if (!(st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC))
3594  read_size += pkt->size;
3595 
3596  avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3597  if (!st->internal->avctx_inited) {
3598  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(avctx, st->codecpar);
3599  if (ret < 0)
3600  goto find_stream_info_err;
3601  st->internal->avctx_inited = 1;
3602  }
3603 
3604  if (pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && st->codec_info_nb_frames > 1) {
3605  /* check for non-increasing dts */
3606  if (st->info->fps_last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
3607  st->info->fps_last_dts >= pkt->dts) {
3608  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
3609  "Non-increasing DTS in stream %d: packet %d with DTS "
3610  "%"PRId64", packet %d with DTS %"PRId64"\n",
3611  st->index, st->info->fps_last_dts_idx,
3612  st->info->fps_last_dts, st->codec_info_nb_frames,
3613  pkt->dts);
3614  st->info->fps_first_dts =
3615  st->info->fps_last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3616  }
3617  /* Check for a discontinuity in dts. If the difference in dts
3618  * is more than 1000 times the average packet duration in the
3619  * sequence, we treat it as a discontinuity. */
3620  if (st->info->fps_last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
3621  st->info->fps_last_dts_idx > st->info->fps_first_dts_idx &&
3622  (pkt->dts - st->info->fps_last_dts) / 1000 >
3623  (st->info->fps_last_dts - st->info->fps_first_dts) /
3624  (st->info->fps_last_dts_idx - st->info->fps_first_dts_idx)) {
3625  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3626  "DTS discontinuity in stream %d: packet %d with DTS "
3627  "%"PRId64", packet %d with DTS %"PRId64"\n",
3628  st->index, st->info->fps_last_dts_idx,
3629  st->info->fps_last_dts, st->codec_info_nb_frames,
3630  pkt->dts);
3631  st->info->fps_first_dts =
3632  st->info->fps_last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3633  }
3634 
3635  /* update stored dts values */
3636  if (st->info->fps_first_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
3637  st->info->fps_first_dts = pkt->dts;
3638  st->info->fps_first_dts_idx = st->codec_info_nb_frames;
3639  }
3640  st->info->fps_last_dts = pkt->dts;
3641  st->info->fps_last_dts_idx = st->codec_info_nb_frames;
3642  }
3643  if (st->codec_info_nb_frames>1) {
3644  int64_t t = 0;
3645  int64_t limit;
3646 
3647  if (st->time_base.den > 0)
3648  t = av_rescale_q(st->info->codec_info_duration, st->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
3649  if (st->avg_frame_rate.num > 0)
3650  t = FFMAX(t, av_rescale_q(st->codec_info_nb_frames, av_inv_q(st->avg_frame_rate), AV_TIME_BASE_Q));
3651 
3652  if ( t == 0
3653  && st->codec_info_nb_frames>30
3654  && st->info->fps_first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE
3655  && st->info->fps_last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
3656  t = FFMAX(t, av_rescale_q(st->info->fps_last_dts - st->info->fps_first_dts, st->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q));
3657 
3658  if (analyzed_all_streams) limit = max_analyze_duration;
3659  else if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) limit = max_subtitle_analyze_duration;
3660  else limit = max_stream_analyze_duration;
3661 
3662  if (t >= limit) {
3663  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "max_analyze_duration %"PRId64" reached at %"PRId64" microseconds st:%d\n",
3664  limit,
3665  t, pkt->stream_index);
3666  if (ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOBUFFER)
3667  av_packet_unref(pkt);
3668  break;
3669  }
3670  if (pkt->duration) {
3671  if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE && pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && pkt->pts >= st->start_time) {
3672  st->info->codec_info_duration = FFMIN(pkt->pts - st->start_time, st->info->codec_info_duration + pkt->duration);
3673  } else
3674  st->info->codec_info_duration += pkt->duration;
3675  st->info->codec_info_duration_fields += st->parser && st->need_parsing && avctx->ticks_per_frame ==2 ? st->parser->repeat_pict + 1 : 2;
3676  }
3677  }
3678 #if FF_API_R_FRAME_RATE
3679  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
3680  ff_rfps_add_frame(ic, st, pkt->dts);
3681 #endif
3682  if (st->parser && st->parser->parser->split && !avctx->extradata) {
3683  int i = st->parser->parser->split(avctx, pkt->data, pkt->size);
3684  if (i > 0 && i < FF_MAX_EXTRADATA_SIZE) {
3685  avctx->extradata_size = i;
3686  avctx->extradata = av_mallocz(avctx->extradata_size +
3687  AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE);
3688  if (!avctx->extradata)
3689  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3690  memcpy(avctx->extradata, pkt->data,
3691  avctx->extradata_size);
3692  }
3693  }
3694 
3695  /* If still no information, we try to open the codec and to
3696  * decompress the frame. We try to avoid that in most cases as
3697  * it takes longer and uses more memory. For MPEG-4, we need to
3698  * decompress for QuickTime.
3699  *
3700  * If AV_CODEC_CAP_CHANNEL_CONF is set this will force decoding of at
3701  * least one frame of codec data, this makes sure the codec initializes
3702  * the channel configuration and does not only trust the values from
3703  * the container. */
3704  try_decode_frame(ic, st, pkt,
3705  (options && i < orig_nb_streams) ? &options[i] : NULL);
3706 
3707  if (ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOBUFFER)
3708  av_packet_unref(pkt);
3709 
3710  st->codec_info_nb_frames++;
3711  count++;
3712  }
3713 
3714  if (eof_reached) {
3715  int stream_index;
3716  for (stream_index = 0; stream_index < ic->nb_streams; stream_index++) {
3717  st = ic->streams[stream_index];
3718  avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3719  if (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL)) {
3720  const AVCodec *codec = find_probe_decoder(ic, st, st->codecpar->codec_id);
3721  if (codec && !avctx->codec) {
3722  AVDictionary *opts = NULL;
3723  if (ic->codec_whitelist)
3724  av_dict_set(&opts, "codec_whitelist", ic->codec_whitelist, 0);
3725  if (avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, (options && stream_index < orig_nb_streams) ? &options[stream_index] : &opts) < 0)
3726  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3727  "Failed to open codec in %s\n",__FUNCTION__);
3728  av_dict_free(&opts);
3729  }
3730  }
3731 
3732  // EOF already reached while reading the stream above.
3733  // So continue with reoordering DTS with whatever delay we have.
3734  if (ic->internal->packet_buffer && !has_decode_delay_been_guessed(st)) {
3735  update_dts_from_pts(ic, stream_index, ic->internal->packet_buffer);
3736  }
3737  }
3738  }
3739 
3740  if (flush_codecs) {
3741  AVPacket empty_pkt = { 0 };
3742  int err = 0;
3743  av_init_packet(&empty_pkt);
3744 
3745  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3746 
3747  st = ic->streams[i];
3748 
3749  /* flush the decoders */
3750  if (st->info->found_decoder == 1) {
3751  do {
3752  err = try_decode_frame(ic, st, &empty_pkt,
3753  (options && i < orig_nb_streams)
3754  ? &options[i] : NULL);
3755  } while (err > 0 && !has_codec_parameters(st, NULL));
3756 
3757  if (err < 0) {
3758  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_INFO,
3759  "decoding for stream %d failed\n", st->index);
3760  }
3761  }
3762  }
3763  }
3764 
3765  // close codecs which were opened in try_decode_frame()
3766  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3767  st = ic->streams[i];
3768  avcodec_close(st->internal->avctx);
3769  }
3770 
3771  ff_rfps_calculate(ic);
3772 
3773  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3774  st = ic->streams[i];
3775  avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3776  if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3777  if (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RAWVIDEO && !avctx->codec_tag && !avctx->bits_per_coded_sample) {
3778  uint32_t tag= avcodec_pix_fmt_to_codec_tag(avctx->pix_fmt);
3779  if (avpriv_find_pix_fmt(avpriv_get_raw_pix_fmt_tags(), tag) == avctx->pix_fmt)
3780  avctx->codec_tag= tag;
3781  }
3782 
3783  /* estimate average framerate if not set by demuxer */
3784  if (st->info->codec_info_duration_fields &&
3785  !st->avg_frame_rate.num &&
3786  st->info->codec_info_duration) {
3787  int best_fps = 0;
3788  double best_error = 0.01;
3789 
3790  if (st->info->codec_info_duration >= INT64_MAX / st->time_base.num / 2||
3791  st->info->codec_info_duration_fields >= INT64_MAX / st->time_base.den ||
3792  st->info->codec_info_duration < 0)
3793  continue;
3794  av_reduce(&st->avg_frame_rate.num, &st->avg_frame_rate.den,
3795  st->info->codec_info_duration_fields * (int64_t) st->time_base.den,
3796  st->info->codec_info_duration * 2 * (int64_t) st->time_base.num, 60000);
3797 
3798  /* Round guessed framerate to a "standard" framerate if it's
3799  * within 1% of the original estimate. */
3800  for (j = 0; j < MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; j++) {
3801  AVRational std_fps = { get_std_framerate(j), 12 * 1001 };
3802  double error = fabs(av_q2d(st->avg_frame_rate) /
3803  av_q2d(std_fps) - 1);
3804 
3805  if (error < best_error) {
3806  best_error = error;
3807  best_fps = std_fps.num;
3808  }
3809  }
3810  if (best_fps)
3811  av_reduce(&st->avg_frame_rate.num, &st->avg_frame_rate.den,
3812  best_fps, 12 * 1001, INT_MAX);
3813  }
3814 
3815  if (!st->r_frame_rate.num) {
3816  if ( avctx->time_base.den * (int64_t) st->time_base.num
3817  <= avctx->time_base.num * avctx->ticks_per_frame * (int64_t) st->time_base.den) {
3818  st->r_frame_rate.num = avctx->time_base.den;
3819  st->r_frame_rate.den = avctx->time_base.num * avctx->ticks_per_frame;
3820  } else {
3821  st->r_frame_rate.num = st->time_base.den;
3822  st->r_frame_rate.den = st->time_base.num;
3823  }
3824  }
3825  if (st->display_aspect_ratio.num && st->display_aspect_ratio.den) {
3826  AVRational hw_ratio = { avctx->height, avctx->width };
3827  st->sample_aspect_ratio = av_mul_q(st->display_aspect_ratio,
3828  hw_ratio);
3829  }
3830  } else if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
3831  if (!avctx->bits_per_coded_sample)
3832  avctx->bits_per_coded_sample =
3833  av_get_bits_per_sample(avctx->codec_id);
3834  // set stream disposition based on audio service type
3835  switch (avctx->audio_service_type) {
3836  case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_EFFECTS:
3837  st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_CLEAN_EFFECTS;
3838  break;
3839  case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_VISUALLY_IMPAIRED:
3840  st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_VISUAL_IMPAIRED;
3841  break;
3842  case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_HEARING_IMPAIRED:
3843  st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_HEARING_IMPAIRED;
3844  break;
3845  case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_COMMENTARY:
3846  st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_COMMENT;
3847  break;
3848  case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_KARAOKE:
3849  st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_KARAOKE;
3850  break;
3851  }
3852  }
3853  }
3854 
3855  if (probesize)
3856  estimate_timings(ic, old_offset);
3857 
3858  av_opt_set(ic, "skip_clear", "0", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
3859 
3860  if (ret >= 0 && ic->nb_streams)
3861  /* We could not have all the codec parameters before EOF. */
3862  ret = -1;
3863  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3864  const char *errmsg;
3865  st = ic->streams[i];
3866 
3867  /* if no packet was ever seen, update context now for has_codec_parameters */
3868  if (!st->internal->avctx_inited) {
3869  if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO &&
3870  st->codecpar->format == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE)
3871  st->codecpar->format = st->internal->avctx->sample_fmt;
3872  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->internal->avctx, st->codecpar);
3873  if (ret < 0)
3874  goto find_stream_info_err;
3875  }
3876  if (!has_codec_parameters(st, &errmsg)) {
3877  char buf[256];
3878  avcodec_string(buf, sizeof(buf), st->internal->avctx, 0);
3879  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3880  "Could not find codec parameters for stream %d (%s): %s\n"
3881  "Consider increasing the value for the 'analyzeduration' and 'probesize' options\n",
3882  i, buf, errmsg);
3883  } else {
3884  ret = 0;
3885  }
3886  }
3887 
3888  compute_chapters_end(ic);
3889 
3890  /* update the stream parameters from the internal codec contexts */
3891  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3892  st = ic->streams[i];
3893 
3894  if (st->internal->avctx_inited) {
3895  int orig_w = st->codecpar->width;
3896  int orig_h = st->codecpar->height;
3897  ret = avcodec_parameters_from_context(st->codecpar, st->internal->avctx);
3898  if (ret < 0)
3899  goto find_stream_info_err;
3900  // The decoder might reduce the video size by the lowres factor.
3901  if (av_codec_get_lowres(st->internal->avctx) && orig_w) {
3902  st->codecpar->width = orig_w;
3903  st->codecpar->height = orig_h;
3904  }
3905  }
3906 
3907 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
3908 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
3909  ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->codec, st->codecpar);
3910  if (ret < 0)
3911  goto find_stream_info_err;
3912 
3913  // The old API (AVStream.codec) "requires" the resolution to be adjusted
3914  // by the lowres factor.
3915  if (av_codec_get_lowres(st->internal->avctx) && st->internal->avctx->width) {
3916  av_codec_set_lowres(st->codec, av_codec_get_lowres(st->internal->avctx));
3917  st->codec->width = st->internal->avctx->width;
3918  st->codec->height = st->internal->avctx->height;
3919  }
3920 
3921  if (st->codec->codec_tag != MKTAG('t','m','c','d')) {
3922  st->codec->time_base = st->internal->avctx->time_base;
3923  st->codec->ticks_per_frame = st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame;
3924  }
3925  st->codec->framerate = st->avg_frame_rate;
3926 
3927  if (st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header) {
3928  st->codec->subtitle_header = av_malloc(st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header_size);
3929  if (!st->codec->subtitle_header)
3930  goto find_stream_info_err;
3931  st->codec->subtitle_header_size = st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header_size;
3932  memcpy(st->codec->subtitle_header, st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header,
3933  st->codec->subtitle_header_size);
3934  }
3935 
3936  // Fields unavailable in AVCodecParameters
3937  st->codec->coded_width = st->internal->avctx->coded_width;
3938  st->codec->coded_height = st->internal->avctx->coded_height;
3939  st->codec->properties = st->internal->avctx->properties;
3940 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
3941 #endif
3942 
3943  st->internal->avctx_inited = 0;
3944  }
3945 
3946 find_stream_info_err:
3947  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3948  st = ic->streams[i];
3949  if (st->info)
3950  av_freep(&st->info->duration_error);
3951  av_freep(&ic->streams[i]->info);
3952  }
3953  if (ic->pb)
3954  av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "After avformat_find_stream_info() pos: %"PRId64" bytes read:%"PRId64" seeks:%d frames:%d\n",
3955  avio_tell(ic->pb), ic->pb->bytes_read, ic->pb->seek_count, count);
3956  return ret;
3957 }

3959 AVProgram *av_find_program_from_stream(AVFormatContext *ic, AVProgram *last, int s)
3960 {
3961  int i, j;
3962 
3963  for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_programs; i++) {
3964  if (ic->programs[i] == last) {
3965  last = NULL;
3966  } else {
3967  if (!last)
3968  for (j = 0; j < ic->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes; j++)
3969  if (ic->programs[i]->stream_index[j] == s)
3970  return ic->programs[i];
3971  }
3972  }
3973  return NULL;
3974 }

3976 int av_find_best_stream(AVFormatContext *ic, enum AVMediaType type,
3977  int wanted_stream_nb, int related_stream,
3978  AVCodec **decoder_ret, int flags)
3979 {
3980  int i, nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
3981  int ret = AVERROR_STREAM_NOT_FOUND, best_count = -1, best_bitrate = -1, best_multiframe = -1, count, bitrate, multiframe;
3982  unsigned *program = NULL;
3983  const AVCodec *decoder = NULL, *best_decoder = NULL;
3984 
3985  if (related_stream >= 0 && wanted_stream_nb < 0) {
3986  AVProgram *p = av_find_program_from_stream(ic, NULL, related_stream);
3987  if (p) {
3988  program = p->stream_index;
3989  nb_streams = p->nb_stream_indexes;
3990  }
3991  }
3992  for (i = 0; i < nb_streams; i++) {
3993  int real_stream_index = program ? program[i] : i;
3994  AVStream *st = ic->streams[real_stream_index];
3995  AVCodecParameters *par = st->codecpar;
3996  if (par->codec_type != type)
3997  continue;
3998  if (wanted_stream_nb >= 0 && real_stream_index != wanted_stream_nb)
3999  continue;
4000  if (wanted_stream_nb != real_stream_index &&
4001  st->disposition & (AV_DISPOSITION_HEARING_IMPAIRED |
4002  AV_DISPOSITION_VISUAL_IMPAIRED))
4003  continue;
4004  if (type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO && !(par->channels && par->sample_rate))
4005  continue;
4006  if (decoder_ret) {
4007  decoder = find_decoder(ic, st, par->codec_id);
4008  if (!decoder) {
4009  if (ret < 0)
4010  ret = AVERROR_DECODER_NOT_FOUND;
4011  continue;
4012  }
4013  }
4014  count = st->codec_info_nb_frames;
4015  bitrate = par->bit_rate;
4016  multiframe = FFMIN(5, count);
4017  if ((best_multiframe > multiframe) ||
4018  (best_multiframe == multiframe && best_bitrate > bitrate) ||
4019  (best_multiframe == multiframe && best_bitrate == bitrate && best_count >= count))
4020  continue;
4021  best_count = count;
4022  best_bitrate = bitrate;
4023  best_multiframe = multiframe;
4024  ret = real_stream_index;
4025  best_decoder = decoder;
4026  if (program && i == nb_streams - 1 && ret < 0) {
4027  program = NULL;
4028  nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
4029  /* no related stream found, try again with everything */
4030  i = 0;
4031  }
4032  }
4033  if (decoder_ret)
4034  *decoder_ret = (AVCodec*)best_decoder;
4035  return ret;
4036 }
4037

4058 int ff_stream_encode_params_copy(AVStream *dst, const AVStream *src)
4059 {
4060  int ret, i;
4061 
4062  dst->id = src->id;
4063  dst->time_base = src->time_base;
4064  dst->nb_frames = src->nb_frames;
4065  dst->disposition = src->disposition;
4066  dst->sample_aspect_ratio = src->sample_aspect_ratio;
4067  dst->avg_frame_rate = src->avg_frame_rate;
4068  dst->r_frame_rate = src->r_frame_rate;
4069 
4070  av_dict_free(&dst->metadata);
4071  ret = av_dict_copy(&dst->metadata, src->metadata, 0);
4072  if (ret < 0)
4073  return ret;
4074 
4075  ret = avcodec_parameters_copy(dst->codecpar, src->codecpar);
4076  if (ret < 0)
4077  return ret;
4078 
4079  /* Free existing side data*/
4080  for (i = 0; i < dst->nb_side_data; i++)
4081  av_free(dst->side_data[i].data);
4082  av_freep(&dst->side_data);
4083  dst->nb_side_data = 0;
4084 
4085  /* Copy side data if present */
4086  if (src->nb_side_data) {
4087  dst->side_data = av_mallocz_array(src->nb_side_data,
4088  sizeof(AVPacketSideData));
4089  if (!dst->side_data)
4090  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4091  dst->nb_side_data = src->nb_side_data;
4092 
4093  for (i = 0; i < src->nb_side_data; i++) {
4094  uint8_t *data = av_memdup(src->side_data[i].data,
4095  src->side_data[i].size);
4096  if (!data)
4097  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4098  dst->side_data[i].type = src->side_data[i].type;
4099  dst->side_data[i].size = src->side_data[i].size;
4100  dst->side_data[i].data = data;
4101  }
4102  }
4103 
4104  av_freep(&dst->recommended_encoder_configuration);
4105  if (src->recommended_encoder_configuration) {
4106  const char *conf_str = src->recommended_encoder_configuration;
4107  dst->recommended_encoder_configuration = av_strdup(conf_str);
4108  if (!dst->recommended_encoder_configuration)
4109  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4110  }
4111 
4112  return 0;
4113 }

4115 static void free_stream(AVStream **pst)
4116 {
4117  AVStream *st = *pst;
4118  int i;
4119 
4120  if (!st)
4121  return;
4122 
4123  for (i = 0; i < st->nb_side_data; i++)
4124  av_freep(&st->side_data[i].data);
4125  av_freep(&st->side_data);
4126 
4127  if (st->parser)
4128  av_parser_close(st->parser);
4129 
4130  if (st->attached_pic.data)
4131  av_packet_unref(&st->attached_pic);
4132 
4133  if (st->internal) {
4134  avcodec_free_context(&st->internal->avctx);
4135  for (i = 0; i < st->internal->nb_bsfcs; i++) {
4136  av_bsf_free(&st->internal->bsfcs[i]);
4137  av_freep(&st->internal->bsfcs);
4138  }
4139  }
4140  av_freep(&st->internal);
4141 
4142  av_dict_free(&st->metadata);
4143  avcodec_parameters_free(&st->codecpar);
4144  av_freep(&st->probe_data.buf);
4145  av_freep(&st->index_entries);
4146 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4147 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4148  av_freep(&st->codec->extradata);
4149  av_freep(&st->codec->subtitle_header);
4150  av_freep(&st->codec);
4151 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4152 #endif
4153  av_freep(&st->priv_data);
4154  if (st->info)
4155  av_freep(&st->info->duration_error);
4156  av_freep(&st->info);
4157  av_freep(&st->recommended_encoder_configuration);
4158  av_freep(&st->priv_pts);
4159 
4160  av_freep(pst);
4161 }

4171 void avformat_free_context(AVFormatContext *s)
4172 {
4173  int i;
4174 
4175  if (!s)
4176  return;
4177 
4178  av_opt_free(s);
4179  if (s->iformat && s->iformat->priv_class && s->priv_data)
4180  av_opt_free(s->priv_data);
4181  if (s->oformat && s->oformat->priv_class && s->priv_data)
4182  av_opt_free(s->priv_data);
4183 
4184  for (i = s->nb_streams - 1; i >= 0; i--)
4185  ff_free_stream(s, s->streams[i]);
4186 
4187 
4188  for (i = s->nb_programs - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4189  av_dict_free(&s->programs[i]->metadata);
4190  av_freep(&s->programs[i]->stream_index);
4191  av_freep(&s->programs[i]);
4192  }
4193  av_freep(&s->programs);
4194  av_freep(&s->priv_data);
4195  while (s->nb_chapters--) {
4196  av_dict_free(&s->chapters[s->nb_chapters]->metadata);
4197  av_freep(&s->chapters[s->nb_chapters]);
4198  }
4199  av_freep(&s->chapters);
4200  av_dict_free(&s->metadata);
4201  av_freep(&s->streams);
4202  av_freep(&s->internal);
4203  flush_packet_queue(s);
4204  av_free(s);
4205 }

4235 AVStream *avformat_new_stream(AVFormatContext *s, const AVCodec *c)
4236 {
4237  AVStream *st;
4238  int i;
4239  AVStream **streams;
4240 
4241  if (s->nb_streams >= FFMIN(s->max_streams, INT_MAX/sizeof(*streams))) {
4242  if (s->max_streams < INT_MAX/sizeof(*streams))
4243  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Number of streams exceeds max_streams parameter (%d), see the documentation if you wish to increase it\n", s->max_streams);
4244  return NULL;
4245  }
4246  streams = av_realloc_array(s->streams, s->nb_streams + 1, sizeof(*streams));
4247  if (!streams)
4248  return NULL;
4249  s->streams = streams;
4250 
4251  st = av_mallocz(sizeof(AVStream));
4252  if (!st)
4253  return NULL;
4254  if (!(st->info = av_mallocz(sizeof(*st->info)))) {
4255  av_free(st);
4256  return NULL;
4257  }
4258  st->info->last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4259 
4260 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4261 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4262  st->codec = avcodec_alloc_context3(c);
4263  if (!st->codec) {
4264  av_free(st->info);
4265  av_free(st);
4266  return NULL;
4267  }
4268 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4269 #endif
4270 
4271  st->internal = av_mallocz(sizeof(*st->internal));
4272  if (!st->internal)
4273  goto fail;
4274 
4275  st->codecpar = avcodec_parameters_alloc();
4276  if (!st->codecpar)
4277  goto fail;
4278 
4279  st->internal->avctx = avcodec_alloc_context3(NULL);
4280  if (!st->internal->avctx)
4281  goto fail;
4282 
4283  if (s->iformat) {
4284 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4285 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4286  /* no default bitrate if decoding */
4287  st->codec->bit_rate = 0;
4288 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4289 #endif
4290 
4291  /* default pts setting is MPEG-like */
4292  avpriv_set_pts_info(st, 33, 1, 90000);
4293  /* we set the current DTS to 0 so that formats without any timestamps
4294  * but durations get some timestamps, formats with some unknown
4295  * timestamps have their first few packets buffered and the
4296  * timestamps corrected before they are returned to the user */
4297  st->cur_dts = RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
4298  } else {
4299  st->cur_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4300  }
4301 
4302  st->index = s->nb_streams;
4303  st->start_time = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4304  st->duration = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4305  st->first_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4306  st->probe_packets = MAX_PROBE_PACKETS;
4307  st->pts_wrap_reference = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4308  st->pts_wrap_behavior = AV_PTS_WRAP_IGNORE;
4309 
4310  st->last_IP_pts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4311  st->last_dts_for_order_check = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4312  for (i = 0; i < MAX_REORDER_DELAY + 1; i++)
4313  st->pts_buffer[i] = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4314 
4315  st->sample_aspect_ratio = (AVRational) { 0, 1 };
4316 
4317 #if FF_API_R_FRAME_RATE
4318  st->info->last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4319 #endif
4320  st->info->fps_first_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4321  st->info->fps_last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4322 
4323  st->inject_global_side_data = s->internal->inject_global_side_data;
4324 
4325  st->internal->need_context_update = 1;
4326 
4327  s->streams[s->nb_streams++] = st;
4328  return st;
4329 fail:
4330  free_stream(&st);
4331  return NULL;
4332 }

4334 AVProgram *av_new_program(AVFormatContext *ac, int id)
4335 {
4336  AVProgram *program = NULL;
4337  int i;
4338 
4339  av_log(ac, AV_LOG_TRACE, "new_program: id=0x%04x\n", id);
4340 
4341  for (i = 0; i < ac->nb_programs; i++)
4342  if (ac->programs[i]->id == id)
4343  program = ac->programs[i];
4344 
4345  if (!program) {
4346  program = av_mallocz(sizeof(AVProgram));
4347  if (!program)
4348  return NULL;
4349  dynarray_add(&ac->programs, &ac->nb_programs, program);
4350  program->discard = AVDISCARD_NONE;
4351  }
4352  program->id = id;
4353  program->pts_wrap_reference = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4354  program->pts_wrap_behavior = AV_PTS_WRAP_IGNORE;
4355 
4356  program->start_time =
4357  program->end_time = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4358 
4359  return program;
4360 }

4392 void av_program_add_stream_index(AVFormatContext *ac, int progid, unsigned idx)
4393 {
4394  int i, j;
4395  AVProgram *program = NULL;
4396  void *tmp;
4397 
4398  if (idx >= ac->nb_streams) {
4399  av_log(ac, AV_LOG_ERROR, "stream index %d is not valid\n", idx);
4400  return;
4401  }
4402 
4403  for (i = 0; i < ac->nb_programs; i++) {
4404  if (ac->programs[i]->id != progid)
4405  continue;
4406  program = ac->programs[i];
4407  for (j = 0; j < program->nb_stream_indexes; j++)
4408  if (program->stream_index[j] == idx)
4409  return;
4410 
4411  tmp = av_realloc_array(program->stream_index, program->nb_stream_indexes+1, sizeof(unsigned int));
4412  if (!tmp)
4413  return;
4414  program->stream_index = tmp;
4415  program->stream_index[program->nb_stream_indexes++] = idx;
4416  return;
4417  }

4424 //+: Return in 'buf' the path with '%d' replaced by a number.
4425 //+: Also handles the '%0nd' format where 'n' is the total number of digits and '%%'.
4426 int av_get_frame_filename2(char *buf, int buf_size, const char *path, int number, int flags)
4427 {
4428  const char *p;
4429  char *q, buf1[20], c;
4430  int nd, len, percentd_found;
4431 
4432  q = buf;
4433  p = path;
4434  percentd_found = 0;
4435  for (;;) {
4436  c = *p++;
4437  if (c == '\0')
4438  break;
4439  if (c == '%') {
4440  do {
4441  nd = 0;
4442  while (av_isdigit(*p))
4443  nd = nd * 10 + *p++ - '0';
4444  c = *p++;
4445  } while (av_isdigit(c));
4446 
4447  switch (c) {
4448  case '%':
4449  goto addchar;
4450  case 'd':
4451  if (!(flags & AV_FRAME_FILENAME_FLAGS_MULTIPLE) && percentd_found)
4452  goto fail;
4453  percentd_found = 1;
4454  if (number < 0)
4455  nd += 1;
4456  snprintf(buf1, sizeof(buf1), "%0*d", nd, number);
4457  len = strlen(buf1);
4458  if ((q - buf + len) > buf_size - 1)
4459  goto fail;
4460  memcpy(q, buf1, len);
4461  q += len;
4462  break;
4463  default:
4464  goto fail;
4465  }
4466  } else {
4467 addchar:
4468  if ((q - buf) < buf_size - 1)
4469  *q++ = c;
4470  }
4471  }
4472  if (!percentd_found)
4473  goto fail;
4474  *q = '\0';
4475  return 0;
4476 fail:
4477  *q = '\0';
4478  return -1;
4479 }
4480 
4481 int av_get_frame_filename(char *buf, int buf_size, const char *path, int number)
4482 {
4483  return av_get_frame_filename2(buf, buf_size, path, number, 0);
4484 }
