4486 void av_url_split(char *proto, int proto_size,
4487  char *authorization, int authorization_size,
4488  char *hostname, int hostname_size,
4489  int *port_ptr, char *path, int path_size, const char *url)
4490 {
4491  const char *p, *ls, *ls2, *at, *at2, *col, *brk;
4492 
4493  if (port_ptr)
4494  *port_ptr = -1;
4495  if (proto_size > 0)
4496  proto[0] = 0;
4497  if (authorization_size > 0)
4498  authorization[0] = 0;
4499  if (hostname_size > 0)
4500  hostname[0] = 0;
4501  if (path_size > 0)
4502  path[0] = 0;
4503 
4504  /* parse protocol */
4505  if ((p = strchr(url, ':'))) {
4506  av_strlcpy(proto, url, FFMIN(proto_size, p + 1 - url));
4507  p++; /* skip ':' */
4508  if (*p == '/')
4509  p++;
4510  if (*p == '/')
4511  p++;
4512  } else {
4513  /* no protocol means plain filename */
4514  av_strlcpy(path, url, path_size);
4515  return;
4516  }
4517 
4518  /* separate path from hostname */
4519  ls = strchr(p, '/');
4520  ls2 = strchr(p, '?');
4521  if (!ls)
4522  ls = ls2;
4523  else if (ls && ls2)
4524  ls = FFMIN(ls, ls2);
4525  if (ls)
4526  av_strlcpy(path, ls, path_size);
4527  else
4528  ls = &p[strlen(p)]; // XXX
4529 
4530  /* the rest is hostname, use that to parse auth/port */
4531  if (ls != p) {
4532  /* authorization (user[:pass]@hostname) */
4533  at2 = p;
4534  while ((at = strchr(p, '@')) && at < ls) {
4535  av_strlcpy(authorization, at2,
4536  FFMIN(authorization_size, at + 1 - at2));
4537  p = at + 1; /* skip '@' */
4538  }
4539 
4540  if (*p == '[' && (brk = strchr(p, ']')) && brk < ls) {
4541  /* [host]:port */
4542  av_strlcpy(hostname, p + 1,
4543  FFMIN(hostname_size, brk - p));
4544  if (brk[1] == ':' && port_ptr)
4545  *port_ptr = atoi(brk + 2);
4546  } else if ((col = strchr(p, ':')) && col < ls) {
4547  av_strlcpy(hostname, p,
4548  FFMIN(col + 1 - p, hostname_size));
4549  if (port_ptr)
4550  *port_ptr = atoi(col + 1);
4551  } else
4552  av_strlcpy(hostname, p,
4553  FFMIN(ls + 1 - p, hostname_size));
4554  }
4555 }
4556 
4557 //+: convert intergers to hex format
4558 //+: s is the total count of numbers in src
4559 char *ff_data_to_hex(char *buff, const uint8_t *src, int s, int lowercase)
4560 {
4561  int i;
4562  static const char hex_table_uc[16] = { '0', '1', '2', '3',
4563  '4', '5', '6', '7',
4564  '8', '9', 'A', 'B',
4565  'C', 'D', 'E', 'F' };
4566  static const char hex_table_lc[16] = { '0', '1', '2', '3',
4567  '4', '5', '6', '7',
4568  '8', '9', 'a', 'b',
4569  'c', 'd', 'e', 'f' };
4570  const char *hex_table = lowercase ? hex_table_lc : hex_table_uc;
4571 
4572  for (i = 0; i < s; i++) {
4573  buff[i * 2] = hex_table[src[i] >> 4];//+: devide 16 to get high hex digit
4574  buff[i * 2 + 1] = hex_table[src[i] & 0xF];//+: residual to get low hex digit
4575  }
4576 
4577  return buff;
4578 }
4579 
4580 int ff_hex_to_data(uint8_t *data, const char *p)
4581 {
4582  int c, len, v;
4583 
4584  len = 0;
4585  v = 1;
4586  for (;;) {
4587  p += strspn(p, SPACE_CHARS);
4588  if (*p == '\0')
4589  break;
4590  c = av_toupper((unsigned char) *p++);
4591  if (c >= '0' && c <= '9')
4592  c = c - '0';
4593  else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')
4594  c = c - 'A' + 10;
4595  else
4596  break;
4597  v = (v << 4) | c;
4598  if (v & 0x100) {//+: if carry is found
4599  if (data)
4600  data[len] = v;
4601  len++;
4602  v = 1;
4603  }
4604  }
4605  return len;
4606 }

4609  unsigned int pts_num, unsigned int pts_den)

4632 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS

4638 void ff_parse_key_value(const char *str, ff_parse_key_val_cb callback_get_buf,
4639  void *context)
4640 {
4641  const char *ptr = str;
4642 
4643  /* Parse key=value pairs. */
4644  for (;;) {
4645  const char *key;
4646  char *dest = NULL, *dest_end;
4647  int key_len, dest_len = 0;
4648 
4649  /* Skip whitespace and potential commas. */
4650  while (*ptr && (av_isspace(*ptr) || *ptr == ','))
4651  ptr++;
4652  if (!*ptr)
4653  break;
4654 
4655  key = ptr;
4656 
4657  if (!(ptr = strchr(key, '=')))//+: find '=', if no '=', exit
4658  break;
4659  ptr++;
4660  key_len = ptr - key;
4661 
4662  callback_get_buf(context, key, key_len, &dest, &dest_len);
4663  dest_end = dest + dest_len - 1;
4664 
4665  if (*ptr == '\"') {//+:The value strings may be quoted and may contain escaped characters within quoted strings.
4666  ptr++;
4667  while (*ptr && *ptr != '\"') {
4668  if (*ptr == '\\') {
4669  if (!ptr[1])
4670  break;
4671  if (dest && dest < dest_end)
4672  *dest++ = ptr[1];
4673  ptr += 2;
4674  } else {
4675  if (dest && dest < dest_end)
4676  *dest++ = *ptr;
4677  ptr++;
4678  }
4679  }
4680  if (*ptr == '\"')
4681  ptr++;
4682  } else {
4683  for (; *ptr && !(av_isspace(*ptr) || *ptr == ','); ptr++)
4684  if (dest && dest < dest_end)
4685  *dest++ = *ptr;
4686  }
4687  if (dest)
4688  *dest = 0;
4689  }
4690 }

4742 int ff_add_param_change(AVPacket *pkt, int32_t channels,
4743  uint64_t channel_layout, int32_t sample_rate,
4744  int32_t width, int32_t height)
4745 {
4746  uint32_t flags = 0;
4747  int size = 4;
4748  uint8_t *data;
4749  if (!pkt)
4750  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
4751  if (channels) {
4752  size += 4;
4753  flags |= AV_SIDE_DATA_PARAM_CHANGE_CHANNEL_COUNT;
4754  }
4755  if (channel_layout) {
4756  size += 8;
4757  flags |= AV_SIDE_DATA_PARAM_CHANGE_CHANNEL_LAYOUT;
4758  }
4759  if (sample_rate) {
4760  size += 4;
4761  flags |= AV_SIDE_DATA_PARAM_CHANGE_SAMPLE_RATE;
4762  }
4763  if (width || height) {
4764  size += 8;
4765  flags |= AV_SIDE_DATA_PARAM_CHANGE_DIMENSIONS;
4766  }
4767  data = av_packet_new_side_data(pkt, AV_PKT_DATA_PARAM_CHANGE, size);
4768  if (!data)
4769  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4770  bytestream_put_le32(&data, flags);
4771  if (channels)
4772  bytestream_put_le32(&data, channels);
4773  if (channel_layout)
4774  bytestream_put_le64(&data, channel_layout);
4775  if (sample_rate)
4776  bytestream_put_le32(&data, sample_rate);
4777  if (width || height) {
4778  bytestream_put_le32(&data, width);
4779  bytestream_put_le32(&data, height);
4780  }
4781  return 0;
4782 }

4784 AVRational av_guess_sample_aspect_ratio(AVFormatContext *format, AVStream *stream, AVFrame *frame)
4785 {
4786  AVRational undef = {0, 1};
4787  AVRational stream_sample_aspect_ratio = stream ? stream->sample_aspect_ratio : undef;
4788  AVRational codec_sample_aspect_ratio = stream && stream->codecpar ? stream->codecpar->sample_aspect_ratio : undef;
4789  AVRational frame_sample_aspect_ratio = frame ? frame->sample_aspect_ratio : codec_sample_aspect_ratio;
4790 
4791  av_reduce(&stream_sample_aspect_ratio.num, &stream_sample_aspect_ratio.den,
4792  stream_sample_aspect_ratio.num, stream_sample_aspect_ratio.den, INT_MAX);
4793  if (stream_sample_aspect_ratio.num <= 0 || stream_sample_aspect_ratio.den <= 0)
4794  stream_sample_aspect_ratio = undef;
4795 
4796  av_reduce(&frame_sample_aspect_ratio.num, &frame_sample_aspect_ratio.den,
4797  frame_sample_aspect_ratio.num, frame_sample_aspect_ratio.den, INT_MAX);
4798  if (frame_sample_aspect_ratio.num <= 0 || frame_sample_aspect_ratio.den <= 0)
4799  frame_sample_aspect_ratio = undef;
4800 
4801  if (stream_sample_aspect_ratio.num)
4802  return stream_sample_aspect_ratio;
4803  else
4804  return frame_sample_aspect_ratio;
4805 }

4807 AVRational av_guess_frame_rate(AVFormatContext *format, AVStream *st, AVFrame *frame)
4808 {
4809  AVRational fr = st->r_frame_rate;
4810  AVRational codec_fr = st->internal->avctx->framerate;
4811  AVRational avg_fr = st->avg_frame_rate;
4812 
4813  if (avg_fr.num > 0 && avg_fr.den > 0 && fr.num > 0 && fr.den > 0 &&
4814  av_q2d(avg_fr) < 70 && av_q2d(fr) > 210) {
4815  fr = avg_fr;
4816  }
4817 
4818 
4819  if (st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame > 1) {
4820  if ( codec_fr.num > 0 && codec_fr.den > 0 &&
4821  (fr.num == 0 || av_q2d(codec_fr) < av_q2d(fr)*0.7 && fabs(1.0 - av_q2d(av_div_q(avg_fr, fr))) > 0.1))
4822  fr = codec_fr;
4823  }
4824 
4825  return fr;
4826 }

4828 int avformat_match_stream_specifier(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
4829  const char *spec)
4830 {
4831  if (*spec <= '9' && *spec >= '0') /* opt:index */
4832  return strtol(spec, NULL, 0) == st->index;
4833  else if (*spec == 'v' || *spec == 'a' || *spec == 's' || *spec == 'd' ||
4834  *spec == 't' || *spec == 'V') { /* opt:[vasdtV] */
4835  enum AVMediaType type;
4836  int nopic = 0;
4837 
4838  switch (*spec++) {
4839  case 'v': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO; break;
4840  case 'a': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO; break;
4841  case 's': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE; break;
4842  case 'd': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA; break;
4843  case 't': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_ATTACHMENT; break;
4844  case 'V': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO; nopic = 1; break;
4845  default: av_assert0(0);
4846  }
4847 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4848 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4849  if (type != st->codecpar->codec_type
4850  && (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN || st->codec->codec_type != type))
4851  return 0;
4852 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4853 #else
4854  if (type != st->codecpar->codec_type)
4855  return 0;
4856 #endif
4857  if (nopic && (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC))
4858  return 0;
4859  if (*spec++ == ':') { /* possibly followed by :index */
4860  int i, index = strtol(spec, NULL, 0);
4861  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++) {
4862 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4863 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4864  if ((s->streams[i]->codecpar->codec_type == type
4865  || s->streams[i]->codec->codec_type == type
4866  ) &&
4867  !(nopic && (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC)) &&
4868  index-- == 0)
4869  return i == st->index;
4870 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4871 #else
4872  if ((s->streams[i]->codecpar->codec_type == type) &&
4873  !(nopic && (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC)) &&
4874  index-- == 0)
4875  return i == st->index;
4876 #endif
4877  }
4878  return 0;
4879  }
4880  return 1;
4881  } else if (*spec == 'p' && *(spec + 1) == ':') {
4882  int prog_id, i, j;
4883  char *endptr;
4884  spec += 2;
4885  prog_id = strtol(spec, &endptr, 0);
4886  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_programs; i++) {
4887  if (s->programs[i]->id != prog_id)
4888  continue;
4889 
4890  //+: stream index of specified program
4891  if (*endptr++ == ':') {
4892 #if MAP_SUPPORT_STREAMTYPE
4893  av_log(s,AV_LOG_DEBUG,"endprt=%s",endptr);
4894  if (*endptr<= '9' && *endptr>= '0') {
4895 #endif
4896  int stream_idx = strtol(endptr, NULL, 0);
4897  return stream_idx >= 0 &&
4898  stream_idx < s->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes &&
4899  st->index == s->programs[i]->stream_index[stream_idx];
4900 #if MAP_SUPPORT_STREAMTYPE
4901  }
4902  else if (*endptr == 'v' || *endptr == 'a' || *endptr == 's' || *endptr == 'd' ||
4903  *endptr == 't' || *endptr == 'V') {
4904  enum AVMediaType type;
4905  int nopic = 0;
4906 
4907  switch (*spec++) {
4908  case 'v': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO; break;
4909  case 'a': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO; break;
4910  case 's': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE; break;
4911  case 'd': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA; break;
4912  case 't': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_ATTACHMENT; break;
4913  case 'V': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO; nopic = 1; break;
4914  default: av_assert0(0);
4915  }
4916 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4917  FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4918  if (type != st->codecpar->codec_type
4919  && (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN || st->codec->codec_type != type))
4920  return 0;
4921  FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4922 #else
4923  if (type != st->codecpar->codec_type)
4924  return 0;
4925 #endif
4926  if (nopic && (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC))
4927  return 0;
4928 
4929  for (j = 0; j < s->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes; j++)
4930  if (st->index != s->programs[i]->stream_index[j])
4931  continue;
4932  //+: did not find the stream index from program stream list
4933  if(j==s->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes)
4934  return 0;
4935 
4936  if (*spec++ == ':') { /* possibly followed by :index */
4937  int k, index = strtol(spec, NULL, 0);
4938  for (k = 0; k < s->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes; k++) {
4939  int ps_idx=s->programs[i]->stream_index[k];//stream index of program
4940 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4941  FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4942  if ((s->streams[ps_idx]->codecpar->codec_type == type
4943  || s->streams[ps_idx]->codec->codec_type == type
4944  ) &&
4945  !(nopic && (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC)) &&
4946  index-- == 0)
4947  return ps_idx == st->index;
4948  FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4949 #else

4951  !(nopic && (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC)) &&
4952  index-- == 0)
4953  return ps_idx == st->index;
4954 #endif
4955  }
4956  return 0;
4957  }
4958  return 1;
4959  }
4960  else
4961  return 0;
4962 #endif
4963  }
4964 
4965  //+: find the right stream from streams of this program
4966  for (j = 0; j < s->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes; j++)
4967  if (st->index == s->programs[i]->stream_index[j])
4968  return 1;
4969  }
4970  return 0;
4971  } else if (*spec == '#' ||
4972  (*spec == 'i' && *(spec + 1) == ':')) {
4973  int stream_id;
4974  char *endptr;
4975  spec += 1 + (*spec == 'i');
4976  stream_id = strtol(spec, &endptr, 0);
4977  if (!*endptr)
4978  return stream_id == st->id;
4979  } else if (*spec == 'm' && *(spec + 1) == ':') {
4980  AVDictionaryEntry *tag;
4981  char *key, *val;
4982  int ret;
4983 
4984  spec += 2;
4985  val = strchr(spec, ':');
4986 
4987  key = val ? av_strndup(spec, val - spec) : av_strdup(spec);
4988  if (!key)
4989  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4990 
4991  tag = av_dict_get(st->metadata, key, NULL, 0);
4992  if (tag) {
4993  if (!val || !strcmp(tag->value, val + 1))
4994  ret = 1;
4995  else
4996  ret = 0;
4997  } else
4998  ret = 0;
4999 
5000  av_freep(&key);
5001  return ret;
5002  } else if (*spec == 'u') {
5003  AVCodecParameters *par = st->codecpar;
5004 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5005 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5006  AVCodecContext *codec = st->codec;
5007 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5008 #endif
5009  int val;
5010  switch (par->codec_type) {
5011  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
5012  val = par->sample_rate && par->channels;
5013 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5014  val = val || (codec->sample_rate && codec->channels);
5015 #endif
5016  if (par->format == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE
5017 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5018  && codec->sample_fmt == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE
5019 #endif
5020  )
5021  return 0;
5022  break;
5023  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
5024  val = par->width && par->height;
5025 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5026  val = val || (codec->width && codec->height);
5027 #endif
5028  if (par->format == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE
5029 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5030  && codec->pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE
5031 #endif
5032  )
5033  return 0;
5034  break;
5035  case AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN:
5036  val = 0;
5037  break;
5038  default:
5039  val = 1;
5040  break;
5041  }
5042 #if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5043  return (par->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE || codec->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE) && val != 0;
5044 #else
5045  return par->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE && val != 0;
5046 #endif
5047  } else if (!*spec) /* empty specifier, matches everything */
5048  return 1;
5049 
5050  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid stream specifier: %s.\n", spec);
5051  return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5052 }

5108 int avformat_match_stream_specifier2(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
5109  const char *spec)
5110 {
5111  if (*spec <= '9' && *spec >= '0') /* opt:index */
5112  return strtol(spec, NULL, 0) == st->index;
5113  else if (*spec == 'v' || *spec == 'a' || *spec == 's' || *spec == 'd' ||
5114  *spec == 't' || *spec == 'V') { /* opt:[vasdtV] */
5115  return avforamt_match_stream_specifier_internal(s,st,spec);
5116  } else if (*spec == 'p' && *(spec + 1) == ':') {
5117  int prog_id, i, j;

5119  spec += 2;

5121  for (i = 0; i < s->nb_programs; i++) {
5122  if (s->programs[i]->id != prog_id)
5123  continue;
5124 
5125  //+: stream index of specified program

5131  stream_idx < s->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes &&
5132  st->index == s->programs[i]->stream_index[stream_idx];

5398  data = avci50_1080p_extradata;
5399  size = sizeof(avci50_1080p_extradata);
5400  } else {
5401  data = avci50_1080i_extradata;
5402  size = sizeof(avci50_1080i_extradata);
5403  }
5404  } else if (st->codecpar->width == 1280) {
5405  data = avci100_720p_extradata;
5406  size = sizeof(avci100_720p_extradata);
5407  } else if (st->codecpar->width == 960) {
5408  data = avci50_720p_extradata;
5409  size = sizeof(avci50_720p_extradata);
5410  }
5411 
5412  if (!size)
5413  return 0;
5414 
5415  av_freep(&st->codecpar->extradata);
5416  if (ff_alloc_extradata(st->codecpar, size))
5417  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5418  memcpy(st->codecpar->extradata, data, size);
5419 
5420  return 0;
5421 }
5422 
5423 #if FF_API_NOCONST_GET_SIDE_DATA
5424 uint8_t *av_stream_get_side_data(AVStream *st,
5425  enum AVPacketSideDataType type, int *size)
5426 #else
5427 uint8_t *av_stream_get_side_data(const AVStream *st,
5428  enum AVPacketSideDataType type, int *size)
5429 #endif
5430 {
5431  int i;
5432 
5433  for (i = 0; i < st->nb_side_data; i++) {
5434  if (st->side_data[i].type == type) {
5435  if (size)
5436  *size = st->side_data[i].size;
5437  return st->side_data[i].data;
5438  }
5439  }
5440  return NULL;
5441 }

5443 int av_stream_add_side_data(AVStream *st, enum AVPacketSideDataType type,
5444  uint8_t *data, size_t size)
5445 {
5446  AVPacketSideData *sd, *tmp;
5447  int i;
5448 
5449  for (i = 0; i < st->nb_side_data; i++) {
5450  sd = &st->side_data[i];
5451 
5452  if (sd->type == type) {
5453  av_freep(&sd->data);
5454  sd->data = data;
5455  sd->size = size;
5456  return 0;
5457  }
5458  }
5459 
5460  if ((unsigned)st->nb_side_data + 1 >= INT_MAX / sizeof(*st->side_data))
5461  return AVERROR(ERANGE);
5462 
5463  tmp = av_realloc(st->side_data, (st->nb_side_data + 1) * sizeof(*tmp));
5464  if (!tmp) {
5465  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5466  }
5467 
5468  st->side_data = tmp;
5469  st->nb_side_data++;
5470 
5471  sd = &st->side_data[st->nb_side_data - 1];
5472  sd->type = type;
5473  sd->data = data;
5474  sd->size = size;
5475 
5476  return 0;
5477 }

5479 uint8_t *av_stream_new_side_data(AVStream *st, enum AVPacketSideDataType type,
5480  int size)
5481 {
5482  int ret;
5483  uint8_t *data = av_malloc(size);
5484 
5485  if (!data)
5486  return NULL;

5488  ret = av_stream_add_side_data(st, type, data, size);
5489  if (ret < 0) {
5490  av_freep(&data);
5491  return NULL;
5492  }
5493 
5494  return data;
5495 }

5497 int ff_stream_add_bitstream_filter(AVStream *st, const char *name, const char *args)
5498 {
5499  int ret;
5500  const AVBitStreamFilter *bsf;
5501  AVBSFContext *bsfc;
5502  AVCodecParameters *in_par;
5503 
5504  if (!(bsf = av_bsf_get_by_name(name))) {
5505  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Unknown bitstream filter '%s'\n", name);
5506  return AVERROR_BSF_NOT_FOUND;
5507  }
5508 
5509  if ((ret = av_bsf_alloc(bsf, &bsfc)) < 0)
5510  return ret;
5511 
5512  if (st->internal->nb_bsfcs) {
5513  in_par = st->internal->bsfcs[st->internal->nb_bsfcs - 1]->par_out;
5514  bsfc->time_base_in = st->internal->bsfcs[st->internal->nb_bsfcs - 1]->time_base_out;
5515  } else {
5516  in_par = st->codecpar;
5517  bsfc->time_base_in = st->time_base;
5518  }
5519 
5520  if ((ret = avcodec_parameters_copy(bsfc->par_in, in_par)) < 0) {
5521  av_bsf_free(&bsfc);
5522  return ret;
5523  }
5524 
5525  if (args && bsfc->filter->priv_class) {
5526  const AVOption *opt = av_opt_next(bsfc->priv_data, NULL);
5527  const char * shorthand[2] = {NULL};
5528 
5529  if (opt)
5530  shorthand[0] = opt->name;
5531 
5532  if ((ret = av_opt_set_from_string(bsfc->priv_data, args, shorthand, "=", ":")) < 0) {
5533  av_bsf_free(&bsfc);
5534  return ret;
5535  }
5536  }
5537 
5538  if ((ret = av_bsf_init(bsfc)) < 0) {
5539  av_bsf_free(&bsfc);
5540  return ret;
5541  }
5542 
5543  if ((ret = av_dynarray_add_nofree(&st->internal->bsfcs, &st->internal->nb_bsfcs, bsfc))) {
5544  av_bsf_free(&bsfc);
5545  return ret;
5546  }
5547 
5548  av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_VERBOSE,
5549  "Automatically inserted bitstream filter '%s'; args='%s'\n",
5550  name, args ? args : "");
5551  return 1;
5552 }
5553 
5554 #if FF_API_OLD_BSF
5555 FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5556 int av_apply_bitstream_filters(AVCodecContext *codec, AVPacket *pkt,
5557  AVBitStreamFilterContext *bsfc)
5558 {
5559  int ret = 0;
5560  while (bsfc) {
5561  AVPacket new_pkt = *pkt;
5562  int a = av_bitstream_filter_filter(bsfc, codec, NULL,
5563  &new_pkt.data, &new_pkt.size,
5564  pkt->data, pkt->size,
5565  pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY);
5566  if (a == 0 && new_pkt.size == 0 && new_pkt.side_data_elems == 0) {
5567  av_packet_unref(pkt);
5568  memset(pkt, 0, sizeof(*pkt));
5569  return 0;
5570  }
5571  if(a == 0 && new_pkt.data != pkt->data) {
5572  uint8_t *t = av_malloc(new_pkt.size + AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE); //the new should be a subset of the old so cannot overflow
5573  if (t) {
5574  memcpy(t, new_pkt.data, new_pkt.size);
5575  memset(t + new_pkt.size, 0, AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE);
5576  new_pkt.data = t;
5577  new_pkt.buf = NULL;
5578  a = 1;
5579  } else {
5580  a = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5581  }
5582  }
5583  if (a > 0) {
5584  new_pkt.buf = av_buffer_create(new_pkt.data, new_pkt.size,
5585  av_buffer_default_free, NULL, 0);
5586  if (new_pkt.buf) {
5587  pkt->side_data = NULL;
5588  pkt->side_data_elems = 0;
5589  av_packet_unref(pkt);
5590  } else {
5591  av_freep(&new_pkt.data);
5592  a = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5593  }
5594  }
5595  if (a < 0) {
5596  av_log(codec, AV_LOG_ERROR,
5597  "Failed to open bitstream filter %s for stream %d with codec %s",
5598  bsfc->filter->name, pkt->stream_index,
5599  codec->codec ? codec->codec->name : "copy");
5600  ret = a;
5601  break;
5602  }
5603  *pkt = new_pkt;
5604 
5605  bsfc = bsfc->next;
5606  }
5607  return ret;
5608 }
5609 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5610 #endif

5629 int ff_parse_creation_time_metadata(AVFormatContext *s, int64_t *timestamp, int return_seconds)
5630 {

5636  *timestamp = return_seconds ? parsed_timestamp / 1000000 : parsed_timestamp;
5637  return 1;
5638  } else {
5639  av_log(s, AV_LOG_WARNING, "Failed to parse creation_time %s\n", entry->value);
5640  return ret;
5641  }
5642  }
5643  return 0;
5644 }

5655 int ff_get_packet_palette(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt, int ret, uint32_t *palette)
5656 {
5657  uint8_t *side_data;
5658  int size;
5659 
5660  side_data = av_packet_get_side_data(pkt, AV_PKT_DATA_PALETTE, &size);
5661  if (side_data) {
5662  if (size != AVPALETTE_SIZE) {
5663  av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid palette side data\n");
5664  return AVERROR_INVALIDDATA;
5665  }
5666  memcpy(palette, side_data, AVPALETTE_SIZE);
5667  return 1;
5668  }
5669 
5670  if (ret == CONTAINS_PAL) {
5671  int i;
5672  for (i = 0; i < AVPALETTE_COUNT; i++)
5673  palette[i] = AV_RL32(pkt->data + pkt->size - AVPALETTE_SIZE + i*4);
5674  return 1;
5675  }
5676 
5677  return 0;
5678 }

5680 int ff_bprint_to_codecpar_extradata(AVCodecParameters *par, struct AVBPrint *buf)
5681 {
5682  int ret;
5683  char *str;
5684 
5685  ret = av_bprint_finalize(buf, &str);
5686  if (ret < 0)
5687  return ret;
5688  if (!av_bprint_is_complete(buf)) {
5689  av_free(str);
5690  return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5691  }
5692 
5693  par->extradata = str;
5694  /* Note: the string is NUL terminated (so extradata can be read as a
5695  * string), but the ending character is not accounted in the size (in
5696  * binary formats you are likely not supposed to mux that character). When
5697  * extradata is copied, it is also padded with AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE
5698  * zeros. */
5699  par->extradata_size = buf->len;
5700  return 0;
5701 }
5702 
5703 int avformat_transfer_internal_stream_timing_info(const AVOutputFormat *ofmt,
5704  AVStream *ost, const AVStream *ist,
5705  enum AVTimebaseSource copy_tb)
5706 {
5707  //TODO: use [io]st->internal->avctx
5708  const AVCodecContext *dec_ctx = ist->codec;
5709  AVCodecContext *enc_ctx = ost->codec;
5710 
5711  enc_ctx->time_base = ist->time_base;
5712  /*
5713  * Avi is a special case here because it supports variable fps but
5714  * having the fps and timebase differe significantly adds quite some
5715  * overhead
5716  */
5717  if (!strcmp(ofmt->name, "avi")) {
5718 #if FF_API_R_FRAME_RATE
5719  if (copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_AUTO && ist->r_frame_rate.num
5720  && av_q2d(ist->r_frame_rate) >= av_q2d(ist->avg_frame_rate)
5721  && 0.5/av_q2d(ist->r_frame_rate) > av_q2d(ist->time_base)
5722  && 0.5/av_q2d(ist->r_frame_rate) > av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base)
5723  && av_q2d(ist->time_base) < 1.0/500 && av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base) < 1.0/500
5724  || copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_R_FRAMERATE) {
5725  enc_ctx->time_base.num = ist->r_frame_rate.den;
5726  enc_ctx->time_base.den = 2*ist->r_frame_rate.num;
5727  enc_ctx->ticks_per_frame = 2;
5728  } else
5729 #endif
5730  if (copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_AUTO && av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base)*dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame > 2*av_q2d(ist->time_base)
5731  && av_q2d(ist->time_base) < 1.0/500
5732  || copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_DECODER) {
5733  enc_ctx->time_base = dec_ctx->time_base;
5734  enc_ctx->time_base.num *= dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame;
5735  enc_ctx->time_base.den *= 2;
5736  enc_ctx->ticks_per_frame = 2;
5737  }
5738  } else if (!(ofmt->flags & AVFMT_VARIABLE_FPS)
5739  && !av_match_name(ofmt->name, "mov,mp4,3gp,3g2,psp,ipod,ismv,f4v")) {
5740  if (copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_AUTO && dec_ctx->time_base.den
5741  && av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base)*dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame > av_q2d(ist->time_base)
5742  && av_q2d(ist->time_base) < 1.0/500
5743  || copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_DECODER) {
5744  enc_ctx->time_base = dec_ctx->time_base;
5745  enc_ctx->time_base.num *= dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame;
5746  }
5747  }
5748 
5749  if ((enc_ctx->codec_tag == AV_RL32("tmcd") || ost->codecpar->codec_tag == AV_RL32("tmcd"))
5750  && dec_ctx->time_base.num < dec_ctx->time_base.den
5751  && dec_ctx->time_base.num > 0
5752  && 121LL*dec_ctx->time_base.num > dec_ctx->time_base.den) {
5753  enc_ctx->time_base = dec_ctx->time_base;
5754  }
5755 
5756  if (ost->avg_frame_rate.num)
5757  enc_ctx->time_base = av_inv_q(ost->avg_frame_rate);
5758 
5759  av_reduce(&enc_ctx->time_base.num, &enc_ctx->time_base.den,
5760  enc_ctx->time_base.num, enc_ctx->time_base.den, INT_MAX);
5761 
5762  return 0;
5763 }
5764
